**The Core Mechanic**

Every roll in Sideros uses the same structure. Roll a d20, add your relevant Attribute modifier, add your Mastery Bonus if proficient, and compare to the Threshold the Game Master sets.

| **Roll d20  +  Attribute Modifier  +  Mastery Bonus (if proficient)  vs  Threshold** *Meet or beat the Threshold to succeed. Common Thresholds: 8 (trivial) · 12 (standard) · 16 (difficult) · 20 (very hard) · 25 (extraordinary).* |
| --- |

**Two types of roll**

| **Active Resonance** You are attempting something — picking a lock, recalling lore, persuading an NPC. Equivalent to an Ability Check. | **Warding Resonance** Something is happening to you — resisting poison, staying conscious under mental assault. Equivalent to a Saving Throw. Each attribute has one. |
| --- | --- |

**Modifying rolls**

| **Resonant Fortune** Roll two d20s and use the higher result. Granted by abilities, favourable circumstances, and Fated Bond relationships. Equivalent to Advantage. | **Resonant Discord** Roll two d20s and use the lower result. Imposed by conditions, environmental penalties, or opposing abilities. Equivalent to Disadvantage. |
| --- | --- |

**The Six Resonance Attributes**

Your six attributes each have a score (typically 8-20 at Depth 1) and a modifier: (score - 10) / 2, rounded down. The modifier is what you add to rolls, not the score.

| **Abbr.** | **Attribute** | **What it covers** | **Key Disciplines** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **FOR** | **Forcefulness** | Raw strength, intimidation, feats of physical power | *Athletics · Intimidation · Grapple · Break* |
| **SWI** | **Swiftness** | Speed, agility, precision, and reaction time | *Acrobatics · Stealth · Sleight of Hand · Initiative* |
| **END** | **Endurance** | Physical resilience, stamina, resistance to harm | *Vitality maximum · Physical Warding Resonances* |
| **ACU** | **Acuity** | Intelligence, memory, perception, and analysis | *Investigation · History · Aetheric Lore · Nature · Perception* |
| **ATT** | **Attunement** | Instinct, empathy, and connection to the Aether and living things | *Insight · Animal Handling · Medicine · Survival · Weaving* |
| **RES** | **Resonance** | Presence, force of personality, and social influence | *Deception · Persuasion · Performance · Fated Bond abilities* |

**Mastery Bonus:** +2 at Depth 1. Increases to +3 at Depth 5, +4 at Depth 9, +5 at Depth 13, +6 at Depth 17. Add your full Mastery Bonus to checks in Disciplines where you are Proficient. Double it for Expertise. Equivalent to Proficiency Bonus.

**Vitality, Guard Rating ****&**** Loom Tests**

| **Vitality (= Hit Points)** Determined by your Path's Vitality Die + Endurance modifier per Depth. When Vitality drops to 0, you make Loom Tests. Three successes stabilise you. Three failures mean death. Natural 20 = regain 1 Vitality and stand. Natural 1 = counts as two failures. | **Guard Rating (= Armour Class)** How hard you are to hit in combat. Base: 10 + Swiftness modifier. Armour adds to this. Some abilities grant Guard Rating from other attributes. An attacker's Strike Resonance (attack roll) must meet or beat your Guard Rating to deal damage. |
| --- | --- |

**Action Economy — What You Can Do on Your Turn**

| **Abbr.** | **Attribute** | **What it covers** | **Key Disciplines** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Act** | **Action** | Your main turn action: attack, use a Path ability, Weave a Working, help, or take any significant action | *One per turn* |
| **Move** | **Movement** | Move up to your speed (typically 30 ft). Split around your Act — move, act, move again. Difficult terrain costs double | *Up to speed/turn* |
| **Instinct** | **Bonus Action** | A fast secondary action: draw weapon, shove, interact with an object. Some abilities specify they require an Instinct | *One per turn* |
| **Reflex** | **Reaction** | Happens on someone else's turn in response to a trigger. Opportunity strikes use a Reflex | *One per round* |

**Weaving — How Magic Works**

Magic is called Weaving. Practitioners Weave a Working (spell) by spending an Aetheric Channel (spell slot). Not every Path can Weave.

| **Aetheric Channels** Your magical resource — equivalent to spell slots. Channels come in tiers (T1-T5). Spend a Channel of the required tier to Weave a Working. Recover all Channels on a Deep Attunement. Some Paths recover partial Channels on Brief Attunement. | **Weaving Threshold** The difficulty number for your Workings (= Spell Save DC). Formula: 8 + Mastery Bonus + Weaving Attribute modifier. Your Path specifies which attribute powers your Weaving. Targets make a Warding Resonance vs this number. |
| --- | --- |

**Aether-Dampening Ore:** Certain locations suppress Weaving entirely — Channels cannot be spent, Workings fail. Dunmarim are immune to Ore. Accord-Makers function at reduced tier rather than failing.

| **Deep Attunement (= Long Rest)** Roughly 8 hours of rest. Recovers all Vitality, all Aetheric Channels, and resets most once-per-rest abilities. | **Brief Attunement (= Short Rest)** About 1 hour of rest. Spend Vitality Dice to recover Vitality. Some Paths (Coil-Stalker, Scion-Pledged) recover their primary resource on Brief Attunement. |
| --- | --- |

**Depth Progression**

Depth is equivalent to Level — 1 through 20 for most Paths, some extending to 30. Your Calling (subclass) is chosen at Depth 3.

| **Sideros Term** | **D****&****D Equivalent ****&**** Notes** |
| --- | --- |
| **Depth 1** | Campaign start. Core Path feature active. Mastery Bonus +2. |
| **Depth 3** | Calling chosen — the specific direction within your Path. Equivalent to a subclass. |
| **Depth 4** | Attribute Score Improvement: +2 to one attribute, or +1 to two. Or take a Feat instead. |
| **Depth 5** | Mastery Bonus increases to +3. Most Paths gain a significant feature here. |
| **Depth 9** | Mastery Bonus increases to +4. |
| **Depth 13** | Mastery Bonus increases to +5. |
| **Depth 17** | Mastery Bonus increases to +6. Legendary-tier abilities unlock. |
| **Depth 20** | Capstone feature — the full expression of the Path's power. |

**Sideros vs D****&****D 5e — Terminology**

If you have played D&D 5e, the mechanics are equivalent — the names are Sideros-native.

| **Sideros Term** | **D****&****D Equivalent ****&**** Notes** |
| --- | --- |
| **Vitality** | Hit Points — maximum set by Path Vitality Die + END modifier per Depth |
| **Guard Rating** | Armour Class — 10 + SWI modifier, modified by armour and abilities |
| **Active Resonance** | Ability Check — d20 + modifier vs a Threshold |
| **Warding Resonance** | Saving Throw — each of the six attributes has one |
| **Mastery Bonus** | Proficiency Bonus — +2 at Depth 1, scales with Depth |
| **Discipline** | Skill — each tied to one of the six attributes |
| **Depth** | Level — 1 through 20 (some Paths extend further) |
| **Path** | Class — 18 Paths available |
| **Calling** | Subclass — chosen at Depth 3 |
| **Kindred** | Race / Species — 20 Kindreds available |
| **Origin** | Background — provides Disciplines, a tool or language, and an Origin Feature |
| **Weaving** | Spellcasting — the act of casting a spell |
| **Working** | Spell — a specific magical effect |
| **Aetheric Channel** | Spell Slot — spent to power Workings; Tier 1-5 |
| **Weaving Attribute** | Spellcasting Ability — the attribute powering your Workings |
| **Weaving Threshold** | Spell Save DC — 8 + Mastery Bonus + Weaving Attribute modifier |
| **Loom Test** | Death Saving Throw — three successes stabilise; three failures mean death |
| **Resonant Fortune** | Advantage — roll two d20s, take the higher |
| **Resonant Discord** | Disadvantage — roll two d20s, take the lower |
| **Deep Attunement** | Long Rest — recovers Vitality and all Aetheric Channels |
| **Brief Attunement** | Short Rest — spend Vitality Dice; some Paths recover resources |
| **Act** | Action — your main turn action |
| **Instinct** | Bonus Action — a fast secondary action |
| **Reflex** | Reaction — triggered response, once per round |
| **Strike Resonance** | Attack Roll — d20 + modifier vs target's Guard Rating |
| **Aetheric Benediction** | Channel Divinity — specific to Zodiac Priest and Oathed Vanguard |

**What makes Sideros different from D****&****D:** Three systems have no D&D equivalent. Fated Bonds (Fate Numbers determine which characters are cosmically drawn together — mechanical benefits and relationship depth). Primal Essence (Alpha, Beta, or Omega — affects how NPCs respond and some biological realities). The Loom of Fate (a cosmic structure with opinions about your character's life — the campaign's central conflict involves an attempt to destroy it entirely).

