**Choose Your Kindred**

Your Kindred is not your personality. It is the Aetheric frequency your body carries — the cosmic inheritance of your lineage that shapes how you interact with the world's forces. A Wolf-Shifter with a gentle soul is still a Wolf-Shifter. A Dunmarim who has left Dunmar is still Aether-hardened. The Kindred is the instrument. You decide how it's played.

| **Human · The Unwritten** d8 · +1 two Attributes · Player's choice No inherited cosmic gifts — which means no inherited limits. Extra Attunement at Depth 1, extra Disciplines throughout, and the unique ability to swap a Mastered Discipline during Brief Attunement. Best for: players who want maximum flexibility. |  |
| --- | --- |

| **Eldren · The Long Memory** d8 · +2 Attunement +1 Acuity Survivors of the Kallos civilization. Born with a Siddha Ambient Working, Attunement Sense (passive Aetheric detection), and once-per-rest access to ancestral memory. Resonant Fortune on ancient history; Resonant Discord on anything newer than 100 years. Best for: deep lore engagement, Omega-aspected scholar. |  |
| --- | --- |

| **Dunmarim · The Ore-Kin** d10 · +2 Endurance +1 Forcefulness Cannot weave Workings — ever. d10 Vitality, natural magic resistance (Working Thresholds −2 against them), Master's Hand crafting, passive ore detection. The only Kindred immune to the Aether's chaos. Best for: the immovable wall who isn't interested in magic. |  |
| --- | --- |

| **Wolf-Shifter · The Two-Skinned** d10 · +2 Forcefulness +1 Attunement The Omote-Ura Gauge — managing tension between human discipline and wolf instinct. Three forms (human/hybrid/wolf) switchable as an Instinct. Pack Resonance, Shōgun-Kami bond, primal senses. Most mechanically demanding Kindred. Best for: resource tension and moment-to-moment roleplay. |  |
| --- | --- |

| **Gear-Forged · The Heart-Born** d10 · +2 Endurance +1 Acuity A constructed being powered by a Resonant Geode heart pre-calibrated to a zodiac sign — born knowing their sign, receive Zodiac Attunement at Depth 1. Frame Modifications as they level. Dormancy (not death) at 0 Vitality. Best for: Jade Empire storyline, questions about personhood. |  |
| --- | --- |

| **Ashé-Touched · The Orisha-Marked** d8 · +2 Resonance +1 Attunement Divine biology — a patron Orisha's energy flows through them visibly. Orisha Domain abilities, Community Root Channel restore, and Living Ashé (2d8 psychic damage entering anti-magic fields). Best for: players who want power that is inherently political. |  |
| --- | --- |

| **Serpent-Kin · The Coil-Walkers** d8 · +2 Attunement +1 Swiftness Ancient civilization, prophetic biology. Natural armor with scale-shedding Reflex, automatic prophetic fragments each rest, amphibious, and The Long Game immunity to being rushed. Best for: the long-game character with patience that unnerves others. |  |
| --- | --- |

| **Avian · The Sky-Kin** d8 · +2 Resonance +1 Swiftness · Fly 30 ft Wings, extraordinary vision, Asha-touched truth sense — always know when being lied to. Judicial Authority (compel one truthful answer per rest), Raptor's Eye, Chinvat Oath-Binding. Best for: social and aerial superiority. |  |
| --- | --- |

| **Fae-Blooded · The Twilight Kindred** d6 · +2 Attunement +1 Resonance · 35 ft Lowest Vitality Die — partially exists in the Otherworld at all times. Twilight Step, Noctilith Resonance, Seasonal Attunement, Fae Bargain (once per session: get almost anything for a personal cost). Vulnerable to unworked iron. Best for: high-risk/high-reward, Otherworld mechanics. |  |
| --- | --- |

| **Moana-kin · The Wayfinders** d8 · +2 Attunement +1 Swiftness · Swim 40 ft Ara Moana navigation system — always know where they are and where everything is going. Two navigation abilities at creation, ocean-adapted body, Pre-Fall Star Charts, Waka Community (Help gives Resonant Fortune to both parties). Best for: the party's compass. |  |
| --- | --- |

| **Te Kapo · The Void-Readers** d8 · +2 Attunement +1 Acuity · Blindsight 30 ft Dark-zodiac perception and Kore-kore void sense — passive detection of hidden doors, invisible creatures, and the Hollow Serpent's movements. Light Sensitive (Resonant Discord in bright light). Best for: the party's eyes in the dark and the Obsidian Deep storyline. |  |
| --- | --- |

| **Lizard-Folk · The Patient Hunters** d10 · +2 Forcefulness +1 Endurance · Regeneration Swamp predators — Bog Predator stealth, Environmental Reading (passive awareness of all creatures within 300 ft), and Regeneration (1 Vitality per Pulse below half; stops with fire). Best for: the wilderness specialist, near-unkillable in prolonged encounters. |  |
| --- | --- |

| **Kuri · The Overlooked** d6 · +2 Swiftness +1 Acuity · Small · 25 ft Social invisibility in urban environments, Infrastructure Knowledge (know the structural weaknesses of any city), Improvisation Mastery, Toxin Resistance. They survive by never being hit. Best for: urban infiltration specialist. |  |
| --- | --- |

**Centaur-Kin · The Steppe-Born**

d10 · +2 Forcefulness +1 Attunement · Large · 50 ft

Fastest Kindred at 50 ft. Charge (+2d6 damage, target prone), Stellar Cartography, Running Dialogue (Resonant Fortune after full-speed move), Natural Archer (ranged strike as Instinct). Cannot enter standard dungeons. Best for: open-terrain dominance.

| **Beast-Descended · The Marked Lineage** d10 · +2 Attunement +1 by Beast lineage Bloodline connection to one of the twelve Legendary Beasts. Twelve lineages (one per zodiac sign), each with a Lineage Breath and unique passive Beast ability. Beast Resonance Pool builds near sacred Beast sites. Fate Number always falls within your Beast's zodiac range. Best for: mythic lineage with ability and complication. |  |
| --- | --- |

| **Geode-Kin · The Constructed Flesh** d10 · +2 Endurance +1 Acuity Fully organic but biologically resonant with Geode frequency — a classified Jade Empire engineering program several generations old. Geode Resonance (Geode-powered items work 1 tier higher), Construct Empathy, Enhanced Frame (+50% Frame Vitality pool). The Jade Empire considers you classified. Best for: organic-but-construct-adjacent, Gear-Forged cold war access. |  |
| --- | --- |

| **Beast-Kin · The Zodiac Morphology** d8 · +2 by morphology · Sign-Locked One of twelve zodiac animal morphologies — partially animal, fully humanoid. Ram-Kin, Bull-Kin, Twin-Kin, Crab-Kin, Lion-Kin, Bee-Kin, Bird-Kin, Scorpion-Kin, Stag-Kin, Goat-Kin, Water-Bearer-Kin, Fish-Kin. Zodiac sign always matches morphology. Legendary Beasts of your sign treat you as familiar. Best for: distinct physical zodiac presence from Depth 1. |  |
| --- | --- |

| **Orc-Kin · The Dispersed People** d10 · +2 Forcefulness +1 Endurance A stateless, dispersed people with no homeland. Relentless Endurance (once per rest, drop to 1 Vitality instead of 0), Menacing Presence (Resonant Fortune on Intimidation after being seen in combat), Pack Tactics (Resonant Fortune on strikes against targets adjacent to an ally). Best for: physically resilient frontline with no institutional allegiances. |  |
| --- | --- |

| **Giant-Kin · The Old Blood** d12 · +2 Forcefulness +1 Endurance · Large-adjacent The highest Vitality Die of any Kindred. Frost giant lineage, Boreal Expanse. Giant's Resilience (cold resistance; Resonant Fortune on extreme environment Warding Resonances), Stone Throw (d10 bludgeoning, 30/60 ft), Jarl's Authority (Resonant Fortune on Intimidation where size matters). Best for: the largest and most resilient character. |  |
| --- | --- |

| **Elemental-Kin · The Aspected Body** d8 · +2 Attunement +1 by aspect Four elemental aspects (Fire, Earth, Air, Water) tied to the four Duchies. Elemental Resistance, Elemental Expression (minor Working once per rest, no Aetheric Channel required), Duchy Attunement (Resonant Fortune on Persuasion and Insight with your Duchy's NPCs). Zodiac sign always falls within your element's Duchy. Best for: elemental identity tied to the Duchy political structure. |  |
| --- | --- |

