**Choose Your Path**

**★ Stellar Cartographer · Fate-Mapper**

d8 · Fate-Knots · Omega

Store natural 20s and 1s as Fate-Knots; redistribute them to any creature within 60 ft. Read Fate Numbers as an Instinct. Map Fated Bonds. Eventually identify Quint Bond cluster members on sight. Callings: Loom's Hand (fate-agent), The Unwritten (fate-eraser, includes Number Masking), Star-Reader (celestial-scholar). Best for: players who want to engage with the Fated Bond system as a core mechanic and enjoy probabilistic manipulation.

**★ Ashé-Medium · The Vessel**

d8 · Ashé Vessel 0–10 · Omega

Invite Orisha presence rather than weaving Workings. Fill the Ashé Vessel through communal acts; spend it on Invocations and Full Possession (Game Master-controlled for 3 rounds). Power cannot be suppressed by Aether-Dampening Ore. Callings: Community Healer, War-Medium, Ancestor-Speaker. Best for: players who want to engage with the Ashélands storyline and enjoy a Path where the power source is relational.

**★ Coil-Stalker · The Controlled Corruption**

d10 · Lead-Scale Gauge 0–20 · Beta

Carry Void-energy as a weapon — the gauge fills with power and approaches dissolution simultaneously. Five corruption stages (Cold/Tempered/Burning/Searing/Void-Husk threshold) each granting escalating combat bonuses and escalating risks. Siderium Quartz reduces the gauge. Callings: Infiltrator, Purgator, Scion-Hunter. Best for: players who enjoy high-risk resource management and want the most morally complex Path in the game.

**★ Geode-Pilot · The Frame-Bonded**

d8 + Frame Pool · Frame Modes · Beta

Bond with a Resonant Geode-powered mechanical Frame — a second body with its own Vitality pool. Three modes (Sentinel/Scout/Resonance), Frame Modifications at every even Depth, Overclock (once per rest), and Resonant Cascade (devastating area discharge). Callings: Sentinel, Engineer, Scout. Best for: players who want a mech-pilot fantasy and enjoy managing a complex secondary system.

**Primal Jarl · The Threshold-Walker**

d12 · Wrath State · Alpha

Highest Vitality Die. Wrath State — release the filter between will and full Aetheric force. Resonant Fortune on Forcefulness, damage resistance, no Weaving abilities while Wrathing. Callings: Berserker (Norse), Steppe Sovereign (Centaur), Beast-Soul (Arcadian). Best for: players who want to be the front-line physical force and enjoy a Path with a clear power fantasy.

**Resonance Seeker · The Harmony-Finder**

d8 · Resonant Chord · Omega

Resonant Chord (bonus die given to any ally per rest — scales from d6 to d12). Frequency Mastery, Countersong. The Path most naturally aligned with the Fated Bond system — Bond Chord gives enlarged dice to Bonded allies. Callings: Lore-Keeper, Valor-Singer, Bond-Harmonist (can facilitate Bond formation). Best for: players who want to support the party and engage with the world's lore and Bond systems.

**Zodiac Priest · The Domain-Tender**

d8 · Aetheric Benediction · Omega · Epic Tier

Tends the memory of what the fallen gods were. Twelve Callings (one per zodiac sign domain). Aetheric Benediction (not suppressible by Ore). Legendary Beast Communion at Depth 7. Domain Embodiment at Depth 17. Epic Tier extends to Depth 30. Best for: players who want the most cosmically connected Path and don't mind that their power grows slowly but reaches extraordinary heights.

**Fade-Guardian · The Veil-Watcher**

d10 · Veil Walk · Omega

Veil Walk (step halfway into the Otherworld), Veil Smite, Seasonal Power (enhanced abilities during birth-tree season). Guards the threshold between worlds. Best for: players who want an Otherworld guardian with deep Tuathan Veil-walking connections.

**Solar Guard · The Prepared**

d10 · Surge of Will · Alpha/Beta

Most versatile warrior. Surge of Will (Vitality restore as Instinct; extra Act 2x/rest). Extra Strikes at Depths 5/11/20. Indomitable (reroll failed Warding Resonances). No cosmic inheritance — pure trained will. Callings: Solar Chivalry, Psi-Warrior (Jade), Runic Knight (Norse). Best for: players who want the highest damage output and fewest mechanical complications.

**Rāśi-Siddha · The Ascetic**

d8 · Tapas Points · Omega · Most Complete

Internal fire as a resource. Three expenditure tiers (Satvic/Rajasic/Tamasic). Kanya Temple can cure Ashen Coil blight-rot. Unarmored Guard Rating from Attunement. Twelve Temple Callings (one per sign). Best for: players who want a discipline-based martial artist with deep connection to the Scattered Temples and zodiac traditions.

**Oathed Vanguard · The Sworn**

d10 · Vitality of the Oath · Alpha

Power contingent on an Oath sworn before the Loom of Fate. Vitality of the Oath (healing pool), Aura of Oath (Warding Resonance bonus to nearby allies). Callings: Solar Compact (devotion), Loom's Justice (vengeance), Ancient Sideros (nature/protection). Best for: players who want an Oath-bound warrior with Sideros-specific cosmic stakes.

**Void-Hunter · The Coil-Tracker**

d10 · Void Quarry · Beta

Void Quarry (bonus damage and tracking against Coil operatives and Void-Husks). Terrain Attunement. Always knows the Quarry's direction within 1 mile. Callings: Void-Slayer, Stalker's Eye, Fang of the Resistance (intelligence network). Best for: players who want to engage directly with the Ashen Coil as their primary antagonist.

**Fate-Breaker · The Probability Thief**

d8 · Probability Strike · Beta

Number Masking (suppress a Fate Number from being read). Probability Strike (bonus damage scaling to 10d6). Cunning Act, Uncanny Dodge, Reliable Discipline. Callings: Probability Thief, Loom Operative (assassin), Street Philosopher (scout). Best for: players who want the rogue fantasy with Fate Number system integration.

**Star-Born · The Uncontrolled**

d6 · Zodiac Surge Points · Omega

Born already weaving — Surge Points convert to/from Aetheric Channels. Wild Surges on natural 1s (or deliberate pushing). Quickened/Empowered/Extended Workings. Callings: Zodiac Bloodline, Wild Surge Master, The Veil-Touched (shadow). Best for: players who want raw weaving power with an element of productive unpredictability.

**Scion-Pledged · The Contract**

d8 · Patron Channels · Omega

Patron Channels (refresh on Brief Attunement — the Patron owns the power). Patron's Mark (free ranged Working). Scion Boons (permanent abilities from deepening the contract). Patrons: Legendary Beast, one of the 13 Scions, or Aethar himself. Best for: players who want the warlock fantasy with high political stakes and a patron relationship that drives campaign plot. Callings: Legendary Beast Pact, Scion Pact, Aethar Pact.

**Comet-Mage · The Formulation Scholar**

d6 · Weave Recovery · Beta

The Kallos-Sworn's scholarly tradition. Formulation Ledger (prepared Workings from research). Weave Recovery (partial Channel restore on Brief Attunement). Three Conclaves as Callings — Shifting Horizons (Aethar's former Conclave), Earthly Core, Veil-Walkers. Best for: players who want the wizard fantasy, Argent Spire storyline access, and depth of Working variety.

**★ Primal Accord · The Accord-Walker**

d8 · Aspect Manifestation · Alpha/Beta split

The Accord-Walker does not worship the Legendary Beasts — they walk in accord with what the Beasts already are. Arcadian theology reads the Pantheonic Fall as a choice: the twelve gods redistributed their divinity into distributed biological presence. Dual resource: Aspect Manifestation (nature Working-equivalents) and Beast Resonance Pool (builds near Legendary Beast sacred sites). Callings: Grove-Tender, Storm-Caller, Moon-Walker, Earth-Shaper, Spore-Accord, Kore-kore Walker, Waka-tōhora. Best for: players who want the Druid fantasy with deep Legendary Beast connections and Arcadia Major storyline access.

**★ Accord-Maker · The Living Machine Tradition**

d8 · Infusions + Blueprints · Beta/Alpha

Approaches the Aether the way a Dunmarim master-smith approaches a difficult alloy — with precise knowledge of its properties and no illusions about who is in charge. Dual resource: Infusion List (temporary Aetheric properties on weapons, armor, items) and Blueprint List (permanent constructs built between sessions, Tier I through V). Operates in Aether-Dampening Ore zones at reduced tier rather than failing. Callings: Alchemist, Architect, Armorer (Dunmarim), Siege Engineer. Best for: players who want the Artificer/Inventor fantasy — rewards between-session preparation.

**Resonance Attribute Generation Methods**

*Choose one of three methods below. All methods produce the same six attributes: Forcefulness, Swiftness, Endurance, Acuity, Attunement, Resonance. After generating base scores, apply your Kindred's bonuses (listed in your Kindred entry). The modifier formula is the same for all scores: modifier = (score - 10) / 2, rounded down.*

**Attribute Score to Modifier Reference**

| **Score** | **Modifier** | **Score** | **Modifier** | **Score** | **Modifier** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **1** | -5 | **2-3** | -4 | **4-5** | -3 |
| **6-7** | -2 | **8-9** | -1 | **10-11** | +0 |
| **12-13** | +1 | **14-15** | +2 | **16-17** | +3 |
| **18-19** | +4 | **20-21** | +5 | **22-23** | +6 |
| **24-25** | +7 | **26-27** | +8 | **28-29** | +9 |
| **30** | +10 |  |  |  |  |

**Method A: The Fated Scores (Recommended)**

| **The Loom's Gift** *The dice set the Loom's pattern. The swap is you. The Kindred bonus is blood. The final number is the soul.* |
| --- |

| **Step** | **Instructions** |
| --- | --- |
| **1** | Roll 4d6 and drop the lowest die. Repeat six times. Record the six results. |
| **2** | Assign each result to one of the six Resonance Attributes in the order you rolled them: Forcefulness, Swiftness, Endurance, Acuity, Attunement, Resonance. |
| **3** | You may swap exactly two scores with each other -- moving one score to a different Attribute. Only one swap is permitted. This represents the soul asserting one truth about itself. |
| **4** | Apply your Kindred's Attribute bonuses to the final scores. Calculate modifiers from the table above. Record all six scores and modifiers on your character sheet. |

**Method B: The Loom's Array (Standard Array)**

Use the following six scores and assign them to attributes in any order: **15, 14, 13, 12, 10, 8**. No swaps needed -- assign freely. This produces a balanced character with one strong focus area and one notable weakness. Good for players who want predictable build math or are creating their first character.

**Method C: Point Buy (Customised Array)**

You have **27 points** to spend. Scores below 8 are not permitted. Scores above 15 (before Kindred bonuses) are not permitted. Spend points from the table below. This produces highly tailored characters at the cost of potential extremes.

| **Score** | **Point Cost** | **Score** | **Point Cost** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **8** | 0 | **9** | 1 |
| **10** | 2 | **11** | 3 |
| **12** | 4 | **13** | 5 |
| **14** | 7 | **15** | 9 |

**Which Attribute to Prioritise**

| **Attribute** | **Primary Paths** | **Governs** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Forcefulness** | *Primal Jarl, Solar Guard, Oathed Vanguard* | Athletics, Intimidation. Melee Strike Resonances and damage for most martial Paths. Primal Jarl adds FOR to damage in Wrath State. |
| **Swiftness** | *Fate-Breaker, Coil-Stalker* | Acrobatics, Stealth, Sleight of Hand. Guard Rating for light armour. Pulse Order (initiative). Ranged attacks for most Paths. |
| **Endurance** | *All Paths equally* | No Disciplines -- expresses through Vitality maximum and Warding Resonances against physical harm, poison, and disease. |
| **Acuity** | *Comet-Mage, Geode-Pilot* | Aetheric Lore, History, Investigation, Nature. Weaving Attribute for intelligence-based Paths. |
| **Attunement** | *Rāśi-Siddha, Zodiac Priest, Stellar Cartographer, Ashé-Medium* | Perception, Insight, Medicine, Animal Handling, Survival. Tapas Points for Siddha. Most healing Paths. |
| **Resonance** | *Resonance Seeker, Star-Born, Scion-Pledged, Ashé-Medium* | Deception, Performance, Persuasion. Fated Bond Active Resonances. Chord Die size for Resonance Seeker. |

**Generate Resonance Attributes**

**Forcefulness-primary Paths**

Physical Force

Primal Jarl, Solar Guard, Oathed Vanguard (for strikes). Put your highest score here if you want to hit hard and often. Forcefulness also governs Athletics and most physical feats of strength. Primal Jarl in Wrath State adds Forcefulness to melee damage — every point matters.

**Attunement-primary Paths**

Cosmic Sensitivity

Rāśi-Siddha, Zodiac Priest, Ashé-Medium, Stellar Cartographer, most Omega Paths. Attunement governs Tapas Points, Perception, Insight, healing, and most Warding Resonances against mental forces. If your Path is about perceiving and responding to the world rather than imposing force on it, Attunement is your primary Attribute.

**Resonance-primary Paths**

Magnetic Presence

Ashé-Medium, Stellar Cartographer, Resonance Seeker, Star-Born, Scion-Pledged. Resonance governs all social Disciplines, the Fated Bond Active Resonances, and Weaving for Paths that use it as their Weaving Attribute. A high Resonance is the difference between a Resonance Seeker who gives their allies d6 Chords and one who gives d12s.

**Acuity-primary Paths**

Pattern Recognition

Comet-Mage, Geode-Pilot. Acuity governs Aetheric Lore, Investigation, History, Nature, and the Weaving Attribute for Paths that draw on analytical intelligence. A high Acuity Comet-Mage prepares more Formulations per Deep Attunement and has a higher Working Threshold for everything they weave.

**Roll once per Attribute · Then swap two scores**

**Roll Your Fate**

Roll 1d100. Record this number — it is yours permanently. It never changes except through extraordinary cosmic intervention.

Your zodiac sign is the cosmic force the Loom has designated you to express. It determines your Zodiac Attunement (Feat) at Depth 4, your Kindred-Zodiac Resonance ability, and which Legendary Beast will eventually recognize you as a peer.

**Determining Sign from Fate Number (optional)**

Loom Method

If you want fate to determine your sign: divide your Fate Number by 100, multiply by 12, round up. Or use this table: 1–8: ♈ Aries · 9–17: ♉ Taurus · 18–25: ♊ Gemini · 26–33: ♋ Cancer 34–41: ♌ Leo · 42–50: ♍ Virgo · 51–58: ♎ Libra · 59–67: ♏ Scorpio 68–75: ♐ Sagittarius · 76–83: ♑ Capricorn · 84–92: ♒ Aquarius · 93–100: ♓ Pisces The Loom method produces a character whose sign and number share a domain — they are doubly designated by the same force.

| *24 Origins — 5 Categories* **ORIGINS** *Step VI of Character Creation* ▸  Scholarly  ·  6 Origins  ·  Comet-Magi Initiate, Kallos-Sworn Initiate,       Siddha Temple Student, Stellar Observer, Loom Analyst, Order Researcher ▸  Merchant  ·  4 Origins  ·  Silk Road Operative, Dunmarim Master-Smith,       Port Damaris Agent, Far-Trade Factor ▸  Shadow  ·  4 Origins  ·  Coil-Adjacent Operative, Trench Keeper Deserter,       Void-Husk Survivor, Kuri Underground Runner ▸  Wanderer  ·  4 Origins  ·  Ceque-Walker, Waka Navigator, Ceque Line Born,       Deep-Road Walker ▸  Marked  ·  6 Origins  ·  Beast Witness, Quint Bond Adjacent,       Orisha-Touched Lineage, Void-Touched Survivor, and more **Note: ***Each Origin includes disciplines, feature, equipment, personality traits, ideals, bond, flaw, and 3 hooks.* | **O** **R** **I** **G** **I** **N** **S** |
| --- | --- |

**Choose Your Origin**

Your Origin is not your Path. It is what came before — the experiences and relationships and choices that made you the kind of person the Path would eventually call. A Comet-Mage with a Merchant Origin brings a particular kind of pragmatism to their formulations. A Primal Jarl with a Scholarly Origin fights differently than one with a Wanderer Origin. The Origin shapes the person; the Path shapes the power.

Your Calling — the specific direction within your Path — is chosen at Depth 3, not Depth 1. This is intentional. The first two Depths of play are the character discovering which aspect of their Path resonates most deeply. You should know your options now (they're listed in the Path document), but the choice itself happens through play.

Choose one of your Path's starting packages, then take the equipment listed for your Origin category. You may also take the starting Gold Marks option instead of your Path's package if you prefer to purchase equipment directly.

Package A (grove-tender / ocean-walker): Leather armor or hide armor, a druidic focus (zodiac-aspected carved wooden staff or beast-talisman), an explorer's pack, a healer's kit (10 uses), a herbalism kit, a Beast-Resonance Journal (blank — for recording Legendary Beast observations during play).

Package B (storm-caller / void-walker): Leather armor, a quarterstaff, a druidic focus, a diplomat's pack, a collection of natural materials from three different ecosystems (Game Master determines significance of each).

Package A (Alchemist / Architect): Leather armor, a dagger, an alchemist's kit, a set of artisan's tools (smith's or tinker's by Calling direction), an explorer's pack, an Infusion Ledger (blank), and one starting Tier I Blueprint (mechanical trap or alchemical device — determined with Game Master at Session Zero).

Package B (Armorer / Siege Engineer): Scale mail (self-modified — includes one built-in Infusion agreed with Game Master at Session Zero), a hand crossbow with 20 bolts, a medium shield, armorer's tools, an explorer's pack, an Infusion Ledger.

**Warrior Path Package**

Primal Jarl · Solar Guard · Oathed Vanguard · Void-Hunter

Package A (front-line): Chain mail or scale mail, a martial weapon of choice, a shield, 5 javelins, an adventurer's pack (bedroll, mess kit, tinderbox, 10 torches, 10 days' rations, waterskin, 50 ft hempen rope). Package B (mobile): Leather armor, two martial weapons, a light crossbow with 20 bolts, an adventurer's pack. Void-Hunter specific addition: A Hunter's Journal (contains notes on one Coil operative's known location — outdated but a starting lead).

**Weaving Path Package**

Comet-Mage · Star-Born · Zodiac Priest · Stellar Cartographer · Ashé-Medium

Package A (scholar): A quarterstaff, a component pouch, an explorer's pack, a Formulation Ledger (Comet-Mage) or ritual journal (other Paths), a set of robes in your house colors (Kallos-Sworn) or plain traveling clothes (others). Package B (traveler): A dagger, an arcane focus (zodiac-aspected crystal or carved wooden focus), a diplomat's pack, a letter of introduction from a relevant institution (Argent Spire, a Scattered Temple, the Ifá tradition). Ashé-Medium specific addition: A ritual bundle (materials for Orisha Invocation — specific to your patron Orisha, assembled with a priest's guidance).

**Skilled Path Package**

Fate-Breaker · Resonance Seeker · Rāśi-Siddha

Package A (performer/operative): A rapier or shortsword, a light crossbow with 20 bolts, leather armor, a musical instrument or thieves' tools (based on Path and Calling direction), an entertainer's pack or burglar's pack. Package B (wandering): Two daggers, leather armor, a lute or deck of fortune-telling cards (narrative item), a diplomat's pack. Rāśi-Siddha specific: No weapon required — unarmed strikes are your weapon. Replace weapon with: a meditation mat, a set of prayer beads (Tapas Point tracking aid), and your Temple's traveler's robe.

**Unique Path Packages**

Coil-Stalker · Geode-Pilot · Scion-Pledged · Fade-Guardian

Coil-Stalker: Dark leather armor, two shortswords, a vial of Siderium Quartz (2 charges — the only thing keeping your gauge in check), a burglar's pack, and a dossier on your current target. Geode-Pilot: Your Resonant Frame (already bonded — it is you), artisan's tools (for Frame maintenance), a navigator's pack, and a letter of introduction from the Jade Empire or the Grand Prime Forgeman (your choice). Scion-Pledged: Any light armor, a weapon of choice, a scholar's pack, and a contract document (sealed — the actual terms are between you and your Patron; the Game Master has seen them). Fade-Guardian: Any armor permitted by your Oath tradition (light, medium, or heavy — your Veil-Walking nature imposes no restriction), a martial weapon, a holy symbol (Otherworld-aspected — a silver branch, a knot-worked disk), a priest's pack.

**The Starting Package**

**Scholarly Origins**

**Comet-Magi Initiate**   Scholarly · Argent Spire

*You trained at Argent Spire — not long enough to reach a significant Circle, but long enough to absorb the Conclaves' framework and leave with something they didn't intend you to keep.*

| **Disciplines:  **Aetheric Lore, History | **Tool / Language:  **Calligrapher's supplies · One of: Old Kallosian, Eldren script, or Conclave notation |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Formulation Fragment** You retain a suppressed Comet-Magi Formulation — a Working the Conclaves consider too dangerous to teach formally. Once per Deep Attunement, attempt to express it: Working Threshold check DC 15. On success: produce a 2nd-tier Working effect (agreed at character creation). On failure: the fragment destabilizes, dealing 1d6 psychic damage. |
| --- |

**Equipment:  ***Scholar's pack, Comet-Magi initiate's robe, personal Formulation Ledger with notes, 15 Gold Marks*

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I quote from texts most people have never heard of — and I know this is irritating. I collect small facts the way other people collect wounds. | Knowledge is the only thing that outlasts catastrophe. The truth is worth knowing even when it costs you peace. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| A mentor at Argent Spire taught me something I'm still working out. | I underestimate things I can't quantify. |

**Narrative Hooks**

▸  *Why did you leave before completing your training?*

▸  *Which Conclave did you align with — and do you still agree with their position?*

▸  *What is in the suppressed Formulation fragment you retained?*

**Siddha Acolyte**   Scholarly · Temple Tradition

*You were raised in or drawn to one of the Twelve Scattered Temples — not as a full Siddha, but as a student who absorbed the tradition's rhythms, mantras, and cosmological framework.*

| **Disciplines:  **Religion (Siddha tradition), Medicine | **Tool / Language:  **Herbalist's supplies · Classical language of your temple's sign-culture |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Temple Blessing** Your sign's Temple has acknowledged your training. Once per Deep Attunement, spend 10 minutes in meditation to invoke your sign's temple blessing — a minor Working effect tied to your sign's domain requiring no Aetheric Channel. Game Master determines the specific effect (Mesha = weapon enhancement; Kanya = remove Corrupted; Vrishchika = read emotional history of touched object; etc.). |
| --- |

**Equipment:  ***Prayer beads, healer's kit (10 uses), traveler's clothes, your sign's temple's foundational mantra text, 10 Gold Marks*

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I find stillness in crisis — which unnerves people who are not still. I treat silence as a complete answer to difficult questions. | Discipline is the only freedom that cannot be taken. The mantra is more honest than the practitioner. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| My teacher's final lesson was unfinished when they died. | I dismiss practical problems that could be solved with less dignity. |

**Narrative Hooks**

▸  *Which temple did you train at — and why did you leave?*

▸  *Do you still practice the mantras? What do they mean to you now?*

▸  *What does the temple want from you that you haven't delivered?*

**Loom Analyst**   Scholarly · Loom of Fate Intelligence

*You worked for the Loom of Fate as an analyst — not field operations, but Fate Numbers, bond patterns, probability clusters. You processed intelligence that would disturb most people. You eventually found something that disturbed you.*

| **Disciplines:  **Investigation, Insight | **Tool / Language:  **Forgery kit · One language of your choice |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Pattern Recognition** When you succeed on an Insight Active Resonance, you may ask the Game Master one yes/no question about whether the situation contains a concealed element — a hidden agenda, a false identity, a missing piece of information. The Game Master must answer honestly. Cannot use this twice in the same scene. |
| --- |

**Equipment:  ***Forgery kit, coded journal (DC 18 to decipher), Loom of Fate contact cipher (reaches a specific handler — if still active), 20 Gold Marks*

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I know more than I should about most people I've just met. I maintain cover habits even when I don't need them. | Information is neutral. What you do with it isn't. The Loom sees all threads — I only needed to see the relevant ones. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| I was assigned to protect someone. I failed. Or I didn't — I'm still not sure. | I compartmentalize too effectively. People feel this. |

**Narrative Hooks**

▸  *What did you find in the Loom's records that you weren't supposed to see?*

▸  *Are you still employed — or did you burn that bridge?*

▸  *Who is attached to your contact cipher, and do you trust them?*

**Order of Pure Reason Researcher**   Scholarly · Dunmarim · Anti-Working

*You were part of the Order of Pure Reason's research division — studying the world scientifically, attempting to explain Aetheric effects through natural philosophy. You have since left, been expelled, or simply stopped believing the Order's conclusions are sufficient.*

| **Disciplines:  **Nature, Investigation | **Tool / Language:  **Alchemist's supplies · Dunmarim technical notation |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Scientific Method** Resonant Fortune on all Warding Resonances against being surprised, Soul-Swayed, or Dread-Struck by Aetheric phenomena — you recognize the mechanism. Additionally: identify any Aetheric Artifact's school and approximate tier by examining it for 1 minute (no Working required). |
| --- |

**Equipment:  ***Alchemist's supplies, research journal (valuable to multiple factions), Order of Pure Reason credentials (opens or closes doors), 15 Gold Marks*

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I ask questions before I act, which sometimes costs me the moment. I am more comfortable with systems than with people. | The truth exists independent of who finds it. A flawed model is better than no model — but only if you know it's flawed. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| A colleague remained inside the Order when I left. I owe them an accounting of what I found. | I require evidence past the point where most people have already decided. |

**Narrative Hooks**

▸  *What did you observe that the Order's framework couldn't explain?*

▸  *The Order considers former members a security concern — are they right to?*

▸  *Your research journal would interest multiple factions. Who knows you have it?*

**Stellar Observer**   Scholarly · Celestial Study

*You spent years watching the sky from a tower, a hillside, or the back of a cart moving between observation points. You think in patterns that span centuries. Most conversations feel short.*

| **Disciplines:  **Aetheric Lore, Perception | **Tool / Language:  **Navigator's tools (star charts, astrolabe) · One additional language |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Celestial Memory** You have memorized the current position of every major celestial body. Under open sky: always know the exact time, date, season, and geographic position — no tools required. Underground or indoors: know precisely how long you've been away from the sky. The Centaur-Kin recognize this as a lesser form of their Stellar Cartography — they are not wrong. Additionally: Resonant Fortune on Aetheric Lore Active Resonances related to astronomical or zodiac timing. |
| --- |

**Equipment:  ***Navigator's tools, a personal star log spanning several years of observations, traveler's clothes, 12 Gold Marks*

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I think in longer patterns than most conversations allow. I note celestial events even when no one asked me to. | The stars don't lie. People do. Pattern is the most honest form of truth. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| Someone funded my observations for years. I don't know why. | I notice the wrong things at the wrong moments — cosmically significant, immediately useless. |

**Narrative Hooks**

▸  *What did you observe in the sky that prompted you to stop watching and start moving?*

▸  *The Great Orrery in Aetheria is the most sophisticated astronomical instrument ever built. Have you seen it?*

▸  *Your star log contains an anomaly from six months ago that you haven't been able to explain.*

**Merchant Origins**

**Silk Road Guild Operative**   Merchant · Trans-Continental Trade

*The Silk Road Guild officially connects every major trading hub in the world. Unofficially, it also moves information, people who need to disappear, and goods that don't appear on manifests. You know which version of the Guild you worked for.*

| **Disciplines:  **Persuasion, Deception | **Tool / Language:  **Navigator's tools · Trader's Common (trade pidgin, understood at all major ports) |
| --- | --- |

| **Origin Feature — Guild Contacts** In any city or major trading post, find a Guild contact within 1d4 hours. The contact can provide: current commodity prices; local political summary; one night's safe house; hiring intelligence. The contact operates on mutual benefit — not loyalty. Asking for something that risks them costs a favor. The Game Master tracks what favors you owe. |
| --- |

**Equipment:  ***Guild signet ring, merchant's scale, letter of credit worth 50 Gold Marks (redeemable at any Guild office), fine clothes, 25 Gold Marks*

| **Personality Traits** | **Ideals** |
| --- | --- |
| I price everything, including things that aren't for sale. I form alliances before I form friendships — both can become the other. | A fair deal is one both parties walk away from having gained something. Movement is safety — anything stationary can be surrounded. |
| **Bond** | **Flaw** |
| Someone on the route still owes me a debt I intend to collect. | I trust negotiation over direct action past the point of usefulness. |

**Narrative Hooks**

▸  *Are you still a Guild operative — or did you leave? If you left, did they let you?*

▸  *Drava Nullsong used Silk Road Guild infrastructure to build the Fang of the Whisper. Do you know something about that?*

▸  *What was the last shipment you moved that you've been trying to forget?*

**Dunmarim Master-Smith**   Merchant · Stone Kingdom Craft

