**Primal Jarl**

*Primal Jarl · Alpha-aspected · Vitality Die: d12*

**Core Mechanic:  **The Wrath State (replaces Rage)  Entering Wrath is not losing control — it is releasing the filter that normally stands between the character's will and the full force of their Aetheric nature. As an Instinct, enter the Wrath State for up to 1 minute. Uses per Deep Attunement: 2 (increases to 3 at Depth 6, 4 at Depth 12, unlimited at Depth 17). While in Wrath State: Resonant Fortune on Forcefulness Active Resonances and Warding Resonances; +2 to melee damage (increases to +3 at Depth 9, +4 at Depth 16); resistance to slashing, piercing, and bludgeoning damage from non-magical sources; cannot enact Workings or use Weaving abilities — the Aetheric field is fully physical. Wrath ends if the character hasn't attacked or taken damage since their last Moment, or if they choose to end it. After W

**Depth Progression**

| **Depth** | **MB** | **Wrath Uses** | **Features Gained** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | +2 | 2 | Wrath State, Unarmored Defense, Danger Sense |
| 2 | +2 | 2 | Primal Endurance (Reckless Attack equivalent) |
| **3** | +2 | 2 | Calling chosen, Calling features (Depth 3) |
| **4** | +2 | 2 | Attribute Score Improvement, Zodiac Attunement (after Legendary Beast encounter), — |
| **5** | +3 | 3 | Extra Strike |
| 6 | +3 | 3 | Wrath Uses → 3, Calling features (Depth 6) |
| 7 | +3 | 3 | Primal Anchor (Feral Instinct equivalent) |
| 8 | +3 | 3 | Attribute Score Improvement, — |
| **9** | +4 | 4 | Brutal Critical (×1 extra die on crits) |
| 10 | +4 | 4 | Calling features (Depth 10) |
| 11 | +4 | 4 | Relentless Wrath (drop to 1 Vitality instead of 0, 1/rest) |
| 12 | +4 | 4 | Attribute Score Improvement, Wrath Uses → 4 |
| **13** | +5 | 5 | Brutal Critical (×2 extra dice) |
| 14 | +5 | 5 | — |
| 15 | +5 | 5 | Eternal Wrath (Wrath no longer ends early) |
| 16 | +5 | 5 | Attribute Score Improvement, Brutal Critical (×3 extra dice) |
| **17** | +6 | 6 | Wrath → Unlimited uses/day |
| 18 | +6 | 6 | — |
| 19 | +6 | 6 | Attribute Score Improvement, — |
| **20** | +6 | 6 | Primal Champion: +4 Forcefulness, +4 Endurance |

**Path Features**

| **Feature** | **Depth** | **Description** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Primal Endurance** | Depth 2 | While in Wrath State, the Primal Jarl may add their Endurance modifier to damage rolls in addition to their Forcefulness modifier. The body's resilience becomes offense — every hit they can take, they can also give. Reckless Strike: before making a Strike Resonance while in Wrath, choose to have Resonant Fortune on that Strike Resonance — all Strike Resonances against you have Resonant Fortune until your next Moment. |
| **Primal Anchor** | Depth 7 | While in Wrath State, the Primal Jarl cannot be moved against their will by any force short of a Legendary Beast. Grapples, shoves, Workings that push or pull — none of them work. The Primal Jarl has planted themselves in the world. Additionally: if a creature tries to grapple the Primal Jarl while they are in Wrath, the Primal Jarl may immediately attempt a counter-grapple as a Reflex. |
| **Eternal Wrath** | Depth 15 | The Primal Jarl may choose to enter a Persistent Wrath State — one that does not end between encounters and lasts until they choose to exit or take a Deep Attunement. While in Persistent Wrath: all Wrath State benefits apply at all times; cannot take Deep Attunement without first ending Persistent Wrath; Forcefulness Active Resonances are always made with Resonant Fortune. The cost: social Disciplines (Persuasion, Deception, Performance) all have Resonant Discord while Persistent Wrath is active. The Aether is fully physical. Words have no weight. |

**Callings**

**Path of the Berserker***  —  Norse Tradition*

**Frenzied Strike (Depth 3):  **Once per Wrath State, make one additional melee Strike Resonance as an Instinct. After Wrath ends, gain one level of Aetheric Depletion — the frenzy burns the body's reserves.

**Mindless Wrath (Depth 6):  **While in Wrath State, immune to Dread-Struck and Soul-Swayed. The Hollow Serpent's whispers cannot find purchase in a mind burning this hot.

**Retaliation Strike (Depth 10):  **When you take damage in Wrath State, you may use your Reflex to immediately make one melee Strike Resonance against the attacker.

**Path of the Steppe Sovereign***  —  Centaur Tradition*

**Battle Cry (Depth 3):  **When entering Wrath State, all allies within 30 ft gain +1d4 to their next Strike Resonance damage roll. The Jarl's surge pulls the pack with it.

**Pack Wrath (Depth 6):  **While in Wrath State, you deal +1d6 damage per ally within 10 ft who is also engaged in melee combat. Maximum +3d6. You fight better surrounded by your own.

**Sovereign's Challenge (Depth 10):  **When entering Wrath State, choose one creature within 60 ft. That creature has Resonant Discord on Strike Resonances against anyone except you until your Wrath ends — the sovereign has claimed priority.

**Path of the Beast-Soul***  —  Arcadian Tradition*

**Beast Aspect (Depth 3):  **When entering Wrath State, choose one Beast Aspect: Ram (charge deals +2d6, target knocked prone); Claw (unarmed strikes deal 1d8 + Forcefulness modifier); Pelt (natural armor, Guard Rating = 13 + Endurance modifier while unarmored). The aspect lasts for the Wrath's duration.

**Bestial Soul (Depth 6):  **While in Wrath State, you can communicate with beasts and they will not attack you unless you attack first. The primal frequency is universal.

**Legendary Beast Empathy (Depth 10):  **When you encounter a Legendary Beast while not in Wrath State, the Beast registers your Beast-Soul aspect and does not immediately classify you as prey. You have one Pulse of safe contact before normal Beast behavior resumes.

**Resonance Seeker**

*Resonance Seeker · Omega-aspected · Vitality Die: d8*

**Core Mechanic:  **Resonant Chord  As an Instinct, the Resonance Seeker strikes a Resonant Chord — a specific harmonic frequency directed at one creature within 60 ft. That creature gains a Resonant Chord Die they may use within the next 10 minutes. Using the Chord Die: Add the Chord Die to one Active Resonance, Strike Resonance, Working Threshold roll, or Warding Resonance roll — after seeing the initial result, before the Game Master determines success. The die is then spent. Chord Die size: d6 at Depths 1–4; d8 at Depths 5–9; d10 at Depths 10–14; d12 at Depths 15–20. Chords available per Deep Attunement: Equal to Resonance modifier (minimum 1). Recharge on Deep Attunement — except: if a creature uses a Chord Die and rolls the maximum value, the Resonance Seeker regains one Ch

**Depth Progression**

| **Depth** | **MB** | **Chord Die** | **Features Gained** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | +2 | d6 | Resonant Chord |
