| **Veil Seal** | Depth 15 | Once per week, the Fade-Guardian may permanently seal a specific Otherworld threshold — a Faerie Mound, a Fade-Bleed zone boundary, or a known crossing point. The seal lasts for one year and one day (a traditional Tuathan binding period), after which it must be renewed. While sealed: no entity may cross the threshold in either direction without the Guardian's explicit permission. A sealed threshold registers on Fae-Blooded perception as an unnatural absence — they feel the doorway and cannot open it. |
