| **Terrain Attunement** | Depth 3 (more at higher Depths) | After spending 1 hour in a terrain type, gain Mastery in Stealth and Perception in that terrain, cannot be tracked through it by non-magical means, and Resonant Fortune on Initiative rolls there. Add two more terrains at Depth 7, one more at Depth 11. |
| **Primeval Awareness** | Depth 6 | Spend one Aetheric Channel to sense Void-Husks, Coil operatives, shapeshifters, and fiends within 1 mile. Sustaining required; lasts 1 minute. Direction but not exact location. |

**Callings**

**Void-Slayer***  —  Combat*

**Colossus Slayer (Depth 3):  **Once per Pulse, when you hit a creature below its maximum Vitality, deal +1d8 additional damage. The Hunter has learned that everything has a threshold — hit something that's already hurting and it hurts more.

**Multiattack Defense (Depth 7):  **When a creature hits you with multiple strikes in one Moment, gain +4 Guard Rating against all subsequent strikes from that creature in the same Moment.

**Stand Against the Tide (Depth 11):  **When a hostile creature misses you with a melee Strike Resonance, you may use your Reflex to make one Strike Resonance against it immediately.

**Stalker's Eye***  —  Ambush*

**Skirmisher (Depth 3):  **When a hostile creature ends its Moment adjacent to you, you may use your Reflex to move up to half your speed. This movement does not provoke Reflex Strikes.

**Sudden Strike (Depth 7):  **When you use the Strike Act while hidden from a creature, you may make an additional Strike Resonance against it as part of the same Act before it can perceive you.

**Ambush Master (Depth 11):  **If you act in the first Pulse of combat while hidden, all Strike Resonances in that Pulse have Resonant Fortune and deal +2d6 damage.

**Fang of the Resistance***  —  Intelligence*

**Coil Network Reading (Depth 3):  **In any settlement, spend 1 hour in observation to identify: whether a Coil operative is present, their approximate Corruption Gauge, and one current Coil objective in this location. You cannot identify who the operative is — only that they're there and what they're doing.

**Counter-Network (Depth 7):  **You have built a loose network of informants across your traveled regions. Once per session, ask the Game Master one question about Coil movements in any location you've spent at least a week in. The answer is current and accurate.

**The Long Hunt (Depth 11):  **You may designate one Scion of the Ashen Coil as a Permanent Quarry — this Quarry designation never expires and cannot be replaced by a new Quarry. The bonus damage against the Permanent Quarry increases to +2d8 and you always know their general continental location.

**Fate-Breaker**

*Fate-Breaker · Beta-aspected · Vitality Die: d8*

**Core Mechanic:  **Probability Strike + Number Masking  Probability Strike: When the Fate-Breaker has Resonant Fortune on a Strike Resonance, or when an ally is adjacent to the target, deal bonus damage: 1d6 at Depth 1, scaling by 1d6 every odd Depth (2d6 at 3, 3d6 at 5, etc., to 10d6 at Depth 19). The damage represents hitting the target at the precise moment when fate aligned against them — not skill, but reading and exploiting probability windows. Number Masking: As an Act (1 minute of subtle manipulation), the Fate-Breaker suppresses one creature's Fate Number — their own or any creature they touch. For 24 hours: the Number reads as static to Fate Number Reading; Bond abilities that require Number-proximity don't register the masked

