**Path Features**

| **Feature** | **Depth** | **Description** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Cunning Act** | Depth 2 | The Fate-Breaker may use the Help, Hide, or Disengage Acts as an Instinct rather than an Act. This is the core efficiency of the Path — the Fate-Breaker never wastes a full action on positioning when a half-action will do. Additionally: the Fate-Breaker may use their Instinct to read one creature's emotional state (fear, aggression, deception, hidden agenda) without an Active Resonance — the probability windows people operate in are readable if you know what to look for. |
| **Uncanny Dodge** | Depth 5 | When the Fate-Breaker can see an attacker, use their Reflex to halve the damage from that attack — they're reading the probability of where the strike will land and not being there. This works against Workings that require a Strike Resonance. It does not work against Workings that only require Warding Resonances — those don't have a physical trajectory to read. |
| **Reliable Discipline** | Depth 11 | When making an Active Resonance in a Mastered Discipline, treat any roll of 9 or lower as a 10. The Fate-Breaker cannot fail at the things they have practiced. The floor rises. This is not luck — it is the accumulated competence of someone who has done this particular thing hundreds of times and knows exactly what a bad roll looks like and compensates for it automatically. |

**Callings**

**The Probability Thief***  —  Arcane Trickster*

**Working Access (Depth 3):  **Gain access to Workings from the illusion and manipulation domains (Mage Hand, Minor Illusion, Disguise Self). These Workings are powered by Aetheric Channels — the Fate-Breaker learns to open them through probability intuition rather than formal training.

**Misdirection (Depth 9):  **Once per encounter, cause a creature that can see you to believe you are in a different location for 1 Pulse. All Strike Resonances against you from that creature during that Pulse automatically miss — they are hitting where you were, not where you are.

**Spell Theft (Depth 13):  **When a creature within 30 ft fails a Warding Resonance against a Working you can see being prepared, you may steal the Working — redirecting its effect to a new target of your choice. Once per encounter.

**The Loom Operative***  —  Assassin*

**Assassination (Depth 3):  **When you attack a creature that has not yet acted in combat (surprise round), Strike Resonances have Resonant Fortune and any hit is automatically a Resonant Strike (maximum damage). Probability fully aligned against a target that isn't ready.

**Infiltration Expertise (Depth 9):  **Create false identities with 7 days of work. The identity includes documentation, established backstory, and contacts who will vouch for it. The Game Master cannot have NPCs see through the identity without specific, targeted investigation beyond routine checks.

**Impostor (Depth 13):  **After 3 hours of careful observation, perfectly replicate a specific creature's appearance, voice, and mannerisms. Combined with Infiltration Expertise, this is the most complete identity toolkit in the game.

**The Street Philosopher***  —  Scout*

**Skirmisher's Eye (Depth 3):  **As an Instinct, disengage and move half your speed — no Reflex Strikes triggered. The Fate-Breaker is never where the danger expects them to be.

**Ambush Coordinator (Depth 9):  **When you initiate an ambush and are hidden, all allies who can see you also count as hidden from the targets for the first Pulse — your positioning reads the field and your body language communicates it to those who know to watch.

**Superior Mobility (Depth 13):  **Movement speed increases by 10 ft. You may move through the spaces of hostile creatures without provoking Reflex Strikes. You may climb and swim at full speed without Active Resonances.

