**Path Features**

| **Feature** | **Depth** | **Description** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Frame Bond ****&**** Geode Pulse** | — | The Pilot bonds with their Resonant Frame — a process requiring 1 week of continuous occupancy and calibration. Once bonded: the Frame responds to thought (no verbal commands needed); the Pilot feels damage to the Frame as phantom pressure (not pain); and the Pilot can sense the Frame's structural integrity without inspection. Geode Pulse (Act, expend Aetheric Channel 1st–3rd tier): The Frame's Geode emits a burst of resonant energy in a 20-ft radius. All creatures make an Endurance Warding Resonance (Threshold = 8 + Mastery Bonus + Weaving Attribute) or take 1d6 thunder damage per Channel tier expended and are pushed 10 ft from the Frame. The damage type may shift to the Geode's zodiac sign type at the Pilot's choice (fire for Aries-calibrated, lightning for Sagittarius-calibrated, etc.). |
| **Frame Modification System** | — | At Depth 1 and every even Resonance Depth thereafter, choose one Frame Modification: Reinforced Plating: +2 Guard Rating in Sentinel Mode Integrated Weapon: one weapon permanently mounted — requires no hands to use Optical Suite: Darkvision 120 ft, or Resonant Fortune on ranged Strike Resonances beyond 60 ft Mobility System: gain climb speed equal to movement, or 30-ft leap as part of movement Resonant Amplifier: +1 to Working Threshold for Geode's sign domain Communication Array: send and receive across the Kelp-Weaver's psychic network Self-Repair Sequence: once per Deep Attunement, Frame Vitality restores 20 points automatically Stealth Field: Frame becomes Aether-Veiled in Scout Mode for up to 1 minute per Deep Attunement Modifications can be reconfigured with 1 week of work and access |
| **Resonant Attunement** | — | The Pilot's Geode and the Frame's Geode begin to harmonize. In Resonance Mode: the Pilot may treat any Working they enact as if opened through the Geode's zodiac sign (adding sign-domain effects to non-aligned Workings). Additionally: the Frame Vitality pool increases by 10 (now Resonance Depth × 5 + 10). Geode Resonance: when the Frame takes damage, the Pilot gains 1 Aetheric Channel of the lowest available tier — the structural stress generates power the Pilot can immediately redirect. Maximum 3 Channels gained this way per Pulse. |
| **Overclock** | — | Once per Deep Attunement: push the Geode beyond safe parameters for 1 minute. During Overclock: Resonant Fortune on all Active Resonances and Strike Resonances; Frame Vitality regenerates 5 per Pulse; all Frame Modifications function at enhanced level (double effects where applicable); the Frame emits light matching the Geode's zodiac color — visible at 300 ft. After Overclock: Frame Vitality drops by 20 immediately (structural strain); no further Overclock until next Deep Attunement maintenance cycle. Gear-Forged Pilots: their Aetheric Overdrive and Frame Overclock share one use between them — they are the same system. |
| **Frame Synchronization** | — | The Pilot and Frame are now so deeply bonded that the Frame responds to subconscious intent. Mode switching is now free — it no longer costs an Instinct. Additionally: the Pilot may enact Workings while in Sentinel Mode without the half-speed penalty — the Frame holds the position while the Pilot's mind reaches elsewhere. Emergency Ejection (Reflex): when Frame Vitality would drop to 0, the Pilot may auto-eject — landing in a safe adjacent space, Frame disabled. The Pilot emerges at full Vitality (the Frame absorbed all the damage). This counts as using the Frame's Vitality as a sacrifice. Cannot be used again until the Frame is fully repaired. |
| **Resonant Cascade** | — | Once per Deep Attunement, the Pilot may trigger a Resonant Cascade — deliberately overloading the Frame's Geode to release all stored Aetheric energy simultaneously. The Cascade: all Aetheric Channels are expended at once; the total energy releases in a 60-ft radius burst dealing 1d8 per Channel tier expended (all targets, Endurance Warding Resonance for half); the Frame is disabled for 1 hour after (needs repair); the Pilot is unharmed inside the Frame's final protective pulse. The Grand Prime Forgeman has used Resonant Cascade exactly once — the site is now a persistent magical anomaly in Antarctos's glacier. |

**Callings**

**The Sentinel***  —  Protector*

**Fire (Depth 3):  **As a Reflex, when an ally within 30 ft is targeted by an attack, you may move up to 15 ft (no Act cost) to interpose the Frame — the attack targets the Frame instead. The movement does not provoke Reflex Strikes.

**Field (Depth 7):  **In Sentinel Mode, all allies within 10 ft of the Frame gain +2 Guard Rating — the Frame's Geode emits a stabilizing resonance field. Passive, no activation required.

**Stand (Depth 11):  **When Frame Vitality drops below 10, Sentinel Mode automatically activates and all Frame Vitality loss is halved until the Frame reaches 0. The Frame burns its last reserves protecting its Pilot and allies.

**The Engineer***  —  Artificer*

**Reconfiguration (Depth 3):  **You may reconfigure one Frame Modification during a Brief Attunement rather than requiring 1 week — the Engineer's intimate knowledge of the Frame allows field adjustments that other Pilots cannot manage.

**Modification (Depth 7):  **One of your Frame Modifications may be active simultaneously with a second that is normally exclusive — you have solved the integration problem that prevents this in standard Frame architecture.

**Design (Depth 11):  **Once per campaign, you may spend 1 month of dedicated work to add a custom Modification designed collaboratively with the Game Master — an ability not on the standard list, derived from your character's specific experiences and the unique properties of your Geode. The Grand Prime Forgeman considers this the only truly interesting question a Pilot ever asks him.

**The Scout***  —  Infiltrator*

**Running (Depth 3):  **In Scout Mode, the Frame makes no mechanical noise — Stealth Active Resonances have Resonant Fortune and the Frame does not trigger vibration-based detection.

**Adaptation (Depth 7):  **The Frame automatically adapts to terrain types encountered. After 1 hour in any specific terrain (underwater, underground, extreme cold, extreme heat), the Frame gains full environmental protection for that terrain type and movement is not impeded.

**Protocol (Depth 11):  **Once per Deep Attunement in Scout Mode, activate for up to 10 minutes: the Frame is completely Aether-Veiled — invisible to sight, magical detection, Attunement Sense, and Te Kapo's Absence Reading. Only Kore-kore perception can detect the Geode's resonance signature, and only if the Te Kapo is specifically looking for it.

**Primal Accord**

*Primal Accord · Alpha/Beta-split · Vitality Die: d8*

**Core Mechanic:  **The Accord-Walker does not call themselves a druid, a shaman, or a nature priest. They call themselves Accord-Walkers — those who walk in accord with what the Beasts already are. The distinction matters. A priest mediates between their congregation and a distant power. An Accord-Walker has no congregation and recognizes no distance. The Legendary Beasts of Arcadia Major — the Nemean Lion, the Queen Bee of the Golden Hive, the Star-Metal Stag — are not objects of worship. They are colleagues, operating at a scale that requires translation rather than reverence.  The Arcadian theology that produces Accord-Walkers begins with a single premise: the Pantheonic Fall was a choice, not a catastrophe. The twelve gods did not lose their divinity. They redistributed it — from concentrated divine form

