**Path Features**

| **Feature** | **Depth** | **Description** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Beast Resonance ****&**** Initial Accord** | Depth 1 | The Beast Resonance system becomes active. Choose one Legendary Beast you have encountered — this is your Primary Beast, your first and deepest accord. You begin with a full pool (5 Resonance Points) for this Beast, and an empty pool for all others. The Beast Resonance system scales with Resonance Depth: pool maximum per Beast increases by 1 at Depths 4, 8, 12, and 16 (maximum 9 at Depth 16). You also gain the Nature Tongue: you can communicate basic intent (not complex language) with any creature whose Beast sign you have encountered. A lion won't carry on a conversation with you, but it will receive a clear non-aggression signal and a specific request for safe passage. More Beasts encountered means more creature-families you can communicate with. |
| **Hive Initiation** | Depth 1 | Through the Bee-Priestess's initiation ritual (completed before or during the campaign's opening), the Accord-Walker gains access to the Hive Attunement system. Begin each session with Hive Attunement equal to half your Attunement modifier (minimum 1, maximum 3). Full restore on Deep Attunement within the Hive's territory; restore half on Deep Attunement elsewhere. The Hive Sense passive: even with 0 Hive Attunement, you always know the number of living creatures within 60 ft — not their position or identity, but their count. The Hive never fully disconnects. |
| **Accord-Walker's Resilience** | Depth 2 | The Accord-Walker's body, repeatedly reconfigured through Aspect Manifestation, develops exceptional physical adaptability. They gain Mastery in all Endurance Warding Resonances. Additionally, they no longer need to make Attunement or Endurance checks to maintain an Aspect when they take damage — the Beast's frequency is stable enough to hold through physical disruption. This replaces the need for Sustained Resonance in Aspect Manifestation; Aspects do not require Sustained Resonance. |
| **Second Beast Accord** | Depth 3 | The Accord-Walker deepens their practice sufficiently to hold attunement with a second Beast simultaneously. They may now have two Beast Resonance pools active at once — one Primary Beast and one Secondary Beast. The Secondary pool begins at the depth of the most recent encounter with that Beast (minimum 1 if encountered at all; 0 if not yet encountered). This is also when the Calling is chosen — the specific expression of the Accord-Walker's practice. The Calling determines which Beast is most accessible and what additional abilities emerge from deeper accord. |
| **Terrain Resonance** | Depth 4 | Choose two terrain types (forest, swamp, grassland, mountain, coastal, underground, arctic, desert). In these terrains: movement not impeded by natural difficult terrain; cannot be tracked by non-magical means; Resonant Fortune on Perception and Survival Active Resonances; Beast Resonance restores +1 per pool during Brief Attunement (in addition to normal restoration). Additional terrain types unlocked at Depths 8 and 12. Terrain Resonance and the grid: An Accord-Walker whose chosen terrain includes the area around an active Ceque Line node feels the node's status immediately upon entering its range. They don't understand what they're perceiving — they feel it as a wrongness or rightness in the terrain, not as Aetheric data. A Ceque-Keeper working with an Accord-Walker in this way gains cr |
| **Hive Memory** | Depth 6 | The Accord-Walker's sustained connection to the Hive has granted them access to its deepest archive — the Queen Bee's memory of what the gods were before they became Beasts. Once per Deep Attunement, by spending 4 Hive Attunement and entering a 10-minute meditation, the Accord-Walker may ask the Game Master one question about what any zodiac force was like in Era I — its original divine nature, its relationship to the mortal world, what it protected, what it feared. The answers are always accurate and always incomplete. The Hive remembered through sensation, not language. The information comes as impressions, emotional weight, and physical memory — not clear statements. An Accord-Walker who receives a Hive Memory and has an Eldren ally may find the two sources (Hive Memory + Ancestral Reso |
| **Beast Chorus** | Depth 10 | The Accord-Walker can now manifest Minor Aspects from two different Beasts simultaneously — wearing one Beast's trait alongside another's. The combinations are limited only by physical compatibility (you cannot have the Nemean Lion's wings and the Crab's full carapace at the same time, but you can have the Lion's golden hide and the Stag's star-sense). Each Minor Aspect costs its normal 1 Resonance Point from the relevant Beast's pool. Additionally: the Accord-Walker may spend 2 Hive Attunement to share an active Minor or Partial Aspect with one willing ally for 1 Pulse — the ally gains the Aspect's physical benefit for that Pulse only. This is the Hive extending what one member has to all members. The ally does not spend Resonance Points; the Accord-Walker's pool sustains the extension. |
| **Full Accord** | Depth 14 | The Accord-Walker has reached sufficient depth of attunement that their Legendary Beast encounters begin to take on a different character. Their Primary Beast now recognizes them as a peer — as a creature expressing its frequency rather than borrowing it. This has practical effects: • The Primary Beast will not attack them under any circumstances (though it may still act aggressively toward their allies). • The Primary Beast may occasionally seek the Accord-Walker out — the Game Master may introduce Beast-initiated encounters where the Beast has information, a request, or simply the desire for contact with the one mortal who expresses its nature accurately. • Legendary Aspect cost for the Primary Beast reduces to 3 Resonance Points. • The Accord-Walker may attempt to request a meeting with |
| **The Living Accord** | Depth 20 | The Accord-Walker's attunement is now so deep that the distinction between their own Aetheric frequency and their Primary Beast's frequency has become genuinely blurred — not erased, but permeable. In practical terms: the Accord-Walker's body shifts subtly toward their Primary Beast's morphology at all times, regardless of active Aspect (the Nemean Lion Accord-Walker has gold in their irises permanently; the Stag Accord-Walker has antler-like bone ridges forming at their temples). These are not threatening — they are recognition marks. Mechanically: The Minor Aspect of the Primary Beast is always active without cost. All Aspect costs for the Primary Beast are reduced by 1 (minimum 1). Once per Deep Attunement, the Accord-Walker may enter a Transcendent Accord — a state lasting up to 10 min |

**Callings**

**The Nemean Calling***  —  Alpha-aspected · Combat*

**Pride's Fury (Depth 3):  **When you manifest a Full or Legendary Aspect and reduce a creature to 0 Vitality in the same Pulse, you restore 1 Resonance Point to the manifested Beast's pool — the kill feeds the accord. Additionally, all allies who witnessed the reduction gain Resonant Fortune on their next Strike Resonance this encounter. The Lion's victory is the pride's victory.

**Apex Predator (Depth 7):  **When in any Full or Legendary Aspect, you cannot be surprised. You always act in the first Pulse of any encounter, regardless of Pulse Order roll. Additionally, creatures below half their maximum Vitality have Resonant Discord on all Strike Resonances against you — the wounded do not challenge the apex without paying for it.

**Legendary Resonance (Depth 11):  **Your Legendary Aspect for any Beast you have encountered at least three times costs 4 Resonance Points instead of 5. Additionally, during a Legendary Aspect, you may spend 2 Hive Attunement to broadcast the Aspect's presence to all creatures within 300 ft — every creature within range becomes instantly aware that something of Legendary Beast frequency is expressing nearby. Most creatures will reconsider their current course of action.

**The Keeper's Calling***  —  Beta-aspected · Stewardship*

**Ecosystem Reading (Depth 3):  **In any natural environment, you automatically know: the health of the local ecosystem (thriving, stable, stressed, or dying); the presence and approximate location of any Aetheric disruption (grid node reactivation, Void-energy contamination, Ashen Coil blight-rot spread) within 1 mile; and which creature in the local ecosystem is in the greatest danger. This is passive, always active, and requires no roll. You are the ecosystem's awareness of itself.

**Restoration Aspect (Depth 7):  **Once per Deep Attunement, when you maintain a Partial or Full Aspect for its full duration without ending it early, the Beast's Resonance pool refills by 2 at the Aspect's end rather than depleting further. The sustained expression deepens the accord rather than drawing it down. Additionally: when you use an Aspect for a purpose that protects or restores the natural world rather than combat, the Hive Attunement cost of any simultaneous Hive ability is reduced by 1.

**Grid Warden (Depth 11):  **Your Terrain Resonance now extends to the Aetheric grid — you can feel Ceque Line nodes within 1 mile as distinct physical sensations, and you know immediately when a node changes state (dormant to active, active to Ophiuchus-reactivating). When you are present at a grid node activation (a Siddha speaking the correct mantra), you may spend 3 Hive Attunement to double the node's effect radius. You have become the living intersection of natural and Aetheric preservation.

**The Bee-Speaker's Calling***  —  Omega-aspected · Communion*

**Hive Mastery (Depth 3):  **Your Hive Attunement maximum increases to 12. The cost of all Hive Attunement abilities is reduced by 1 (minimum 1). Additionally: once per Brief Attunement, you may spend 1 Hive Attunement to instantly know one specific piece of information about any creature you can currently sense through Hive Sense (their Vitality level, their current intent, their Fate Number, or their emotional state — choose one per use).

**Communal Memory (Depth 7):  **The Hive's distributed memory is now accessible to you as a research tool. Once per session, by spending 4 Hive Attunement and 1 hour in communion, you may ask the Game Master one question about any event that occurred within the Queen Bee's 40-mile territory at any point in the last 500 years. The Hive was there. The Hive saw it. The Hive's answer comes in sensory impressions, but it comes accurately. Additionally: you may now share Hive Attunement with a willing ally — transfer up to 3 points of your current pool to them; they may spend it as you would for 24 hours. The Hive recognizes them 

**The Queen's Voice (Depth 11):  **Once per Deep Attunement, you may speak with the Queen Bee's full authority for 1 minute — your words carry the weight of the Hive's 4,000-year accumulated consciousness. During this time: any creature that hears you speak may not attack you or any creature you designate as protected (DC 18 Resonance Warding Resonance to resist — this is the Hive's collective will, not a Working); you may end any ongoing conflict between creatures within 60 ft by declaring the conflict finished (same Warding Resonance to resist). This is not compulsion — it is the weight of something very old and very certain 

**Accord-Maker**

*Base: Artificer · Beta/Alpha · Vitality Die: d8*

**Core Mechanic:  **Every other Path in Sideros approaches the Aether with some form of submission — the Comet-Mage studies it, the Zodiac Priest serves it, the Star-Born was born into it, the Scion-Pledged bargains with things that channel it. The Accord-Maker does none of these things. They approach the Aether the way a Dunmarim master-smith approaches a difficult alloy: with precise knowledge of its properties, respect for what it will and won't do, and no illusions about who is in charge of the conversation. The Aether is not in charge. The Accord-Maker is.  The tradition emerged from two independent sources that arrived at the same conclusion by different routes. The Dunmarim apothecaries discovered, centuries after the Pantheonic Fall, that certain mineral combinations created chemical reactions that pr

