**Currency, Economy, and Magical Materials**

*The global economy is at a tipping point. Gold is destabilising. The real wealth is in magical minerals and survival-critical resources -- those who control Aether-Dampening Ore, Resonant Geodes, or Moon-Petal Lotus hold more real power than any gold-backed throne.*

**Duchy Compact Standard**

| **Denomination** | **Exchange / Notes** |
| --- | --- |
| **Copper Coin (cp)** | 100 cp = 1 Silver Mark |
| **Silver Mark (sm)** | 10 sm = 1 Gold Mark |
| **Gold Mark (gm)** | Standard trade unit — accepted region-wide |
| **Platinum Crown (pc)** | 10 gm = 1 pc — rarely handled |

**Magical Materials Economy**

| *These materials now drive the real economy. A party that controls even a small supply of Weep-Stone or Black Iron has leverage that gold cannot replicate.* |
| --- |

| **Material** | **Value** | **Notes** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Weep-Stone (Siderium Quartz)** | 400 gm / charge | 3 charges per stone. Each charge: -2 Lead-Scale Corruption (Coil-Stalker); disrupts Void-Husk coordination; Kanya purification component. K'uh-la'an uses it as primary currency. |
| **Black Iron** | 80-120 gm/lb equivalent | Not for sale in standard markets. Dunmarim barter only. Retains full effectiveness in Aether-Dampening Ore zones -- the only common weapon material that does. Bladed weapons hold edge far longer than surface-mined iron. |
| **Moon-Petal Lotus** | Strategic / rare | Life-extending herb. Primary commodity of the Southern Sea Circuit. A single dried bloom: 800-1,200 gm in Terra Firma. Strategic commodity -- those who control it effectively control lifespan for the wealthy. |
| **Resonant Geodes** | Strategic asset | Powers Gear-Forged frames. Accord-Maker construction material. Not freely sold -- controlled by Geode-Pilot factions and precursor-site excavation operations. A Tier III Geode: 2,000 gm equivalent minimum. |
| **Aether-Dampening Ore** | Controlled resource | Not for sale openly. Dunmarim and Republic of Argentum control supply. Refined Ore: 5,000+ gm per unit for grey-market buyers. The Coil acquires it through Dunmarim double-agents. |
| **Sun-Kissed Adamas** | 10,000+ gm/lb (worked) | Raw crystal: strategic asset held by Khem-Ma'at Dragon Lords. Worked metal (solar-forged): fewer than a dozen pieces in the known world. +2 Strike Resonances; deals radiant damage; auto-succeeds vs. Void-Husks. |
| **Noctilith (Moon-Stone)** | 200-500 gm / palm-sized piece | Tuathan Archipelago pearlescent stone. Powerful Working focus for illusion. Has no monetary value within Tuathan culture -- value entirely external to practitioners. |

**Cost of Living**

| **Lifestyle** | **Cost/Day** | **What It Provides** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Wretched** | Free | Sleeping rough. END Warding Resonance DC 10 weekly or gain 1 Exhaustion. |
| **Squalid** | 1 sm/day | Flophouse or stable. Adequate to survive. |
| **Poor** | 5 sm/day | Shared lodging, simple meals. Most laborers. |
| **Modest** | 1 gm/day | Private room, decent meals, stabling for a horse. |
| **Comfortable** | 2 gm/day | Good inn, quality food, minor luxuries. |
| **Wealthy** | 4 gm/day | Fine accommodation, servants available. |
| **Aristocratic** | 10+ gm/day | Private manor, personal staff, all social access. |

