**Disciplines Reference**

*Disciplines are Sideros's equivalent of skills. When your character attempts a task requiring particular training or expertise, you make an Active Resonance: roll d20 + relevant Attribute modifier. If you have Mastery in that Discipline, also add your Mastery Bonus. Without Mastery, you add no bonus beyond the Attribute modifier.*

| **Discipline** | **Attribute** | **What It Covers** |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Athletics** | Forcefulness | Climbing difficult surfaces, swimming in currents, jumping for distance or height, any feat of sustained physical effort, grappling, breaking objects |  |
| **Intimidation** | Forcefulness | Threatening someone into compliance, projecting physical menace, coercing through implied force, interrogation through fear |  |
| **Acrobatics** | Swiftness | Keeping balance on unstable surfaces, tumbling past enemies, staying upright when knocked, performing agile stunts |  |
| **Sleight of Hand** | Swiftness | Pickpocketing, prestidigitation, planting objects on others, palming items, subtle manual work without being seen |  |
| **Stealth** | Swiftness | Moving without being seen or heard, hiding, tailing someone without detection, operating quietly in hostile territory |  |
| **Animal Handling** | Attunement | Calming frightened animals, directing trained creatures, reading animal intent, working with mounts under pressure |  |
| **Insight** | Attunement | Reading true intent beneath words, sensing when someone is lying, understanding emotional states, noticing behavioral tells |  |
| **Medicine** | Attunement | Diagnosing illness and injury, stabilising the Loom-Tested, treating conditions, understanding the body's functioning |  |
| **Perception** | Attunement | Noticing things -- visually, aurally, or through Aetheric sensitivity. Passive Perception (Ambient Attunement) applies without a roll |  |
| **Survival** | Attunement | Tracking, foraging, navigating wilderness, identifying signs of Void-Husk activity, reading weather and terrain |  |
| **Aetheric Lore** | Acuity | Working knowledge of magic systems, zodiac theory, Precursor history, Coil operations, Ceque grid structure, Legendary Beasts |  |
| **History** | Acuity | Events, dynasties, institutional structures, notable figures, wars, treaties -- especially the 4,000 years since the Pantheonic Fall |  |
| **Investigation** | Acuity | Finding clues in a location, deducing from evidence, reconstructing events, searching systematically, noticing what is absent |  |
| **Nature** | Acuity | Plant and animal identification, terrain and climate knowledge, agricultural and ecological systems, wilderness lore outside Survival |  |
| **Deception** | Resonance | Lying convincingly, maintaining cover identities, misdirection, false impressions, manipulation without obvious force |  |
| **Performance** | Resonance | Entertaining audiences, inspiring crowds, musical and theatrical skill, oratory, capturing and directing emotional response |  |
| **Persuasion** | Resonance | Convincing through reasoned argument, negotiating, charming, building rapport, affecting group opinion |  |

**Endurance has no Discipline list. It expresses directly through Vitality maximum and Warding Resonances against physical threats.**

**Mastery vs. Half-Mastery vs. Unmastered**

| **Level** | **Effect** |
| --- | --- |
| **Mastered** | Add your full Mastery Bonus to the Active Resonance roll. This represents trained, consistent expertise. |
| **Half-Mastered** | Add half your Mastery Bonus (rounded down). Represents general familiarity without dedicated training. |
| **Unmastered** | Add no bonus beyond the Attribute modifier. High Attributes still help -- the formula is d20 + Attribute modifier only. |

| **Threshold Name** | **Target Number** |
| --- | --- |
| **Simple** | 8 -- routine tasks under pressure, or trivial tasks in difficult conditions |
| **Moderate** | 12 -- professional-level tasks, or routine tasks in genuinely hostile conditions |
| **Demanding** | 16 -- expert-level, or tasks at the edge of normal human capability |
| **Formidable** | 20 -- exceptional performance; the best in a region could achieve this |
| **Legendary** | 25 -- historic achievement; remembered for generations |
| **Void-Touched** | 30 -- beyond normal mortal capability; requires Aetheric enhancement or extraordinary circumstances |

**General Feats**

*At Attribute Score Improvement Depths (4, 8, 12, 16, 19) you may take a General Feat instead of the +2 attribute increase. Feats marked with a minimum Depth cannot be taken before that Depth. Zodiac Attunement Feats (in the Combat Reference section) are separate and not listed here.*

| **Feat** | **Min Depth** | **Effect** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Heightened Awareness** | 1 | You cannot be Surprised. Add +5 to your Pulse Order (initiative) rolls. |
| **Iron Body** | 1 | +2 Vitality at this Depth and at every subsequent Depth you gain. Retroactively add +2 per Depth already gained. |
| **Fluid Motion** | 1 | +10 ft to your movement Speed. When you Dash, Disengage costs no additional Act -- you move freely away from any threat. |
| **Well-Rounded** | 1 | Gain Mastery in any three Disciplines you are currently Unmastered in. Must be in three different Attributes. |
| **Far Reach** | 1 | Ranged Strike Resonances ignore the penalty for long range. You may shoot through partial cover without Resonant Discord. |
| **Battle-Weaver** | 1 | Prerequisite: Weave-capable. You may maintain Sustained Resonance (concentration) through taking damage -- make an END Warding Resonance (DC 10 or half damage, whichever is higher) to hold it. You may also expend a Channel as a Reflex action. |
| **Dual Resonance** | 1 | When wielding two Mastered one-handed weapons, both count as Mastered for attack and damage. You may draw two weapons simultaneously. |
| **Stand Firm** | 1 | Creatures you hit with Opportunity Strikes do not reduce their movement speed. When a creature within 5 ft of you is attacked, you may use your Reflex to make a Strike Resonance against the attacker. |
| **Inspiring Presence** | 1 | After a 10-minute speech to up to 6 willing creatures who can hear you, each gains temporary Vitality equal to your Resonance modifier + your Depth. Lasts until Brief Attunement. Cannot use this again until you complete a Deep Attunement. |
| **Resilient** | 1 | Choose one Attribute. Gain Half-Mastery in Warding Resonances for that Attribute. If you already have Half-Mastery, gain full Mastery. |
| **Primal Power** | 1 | Prerequisite: Forcefulness 13. Before you make a melee Strike Resonance with a heavy two-handed weapon, you may declare a Power Strike: accept Resonant Discord on the attack roll; on a hit, add your Mastery Bonus to damage again. |
| **Keen Observer** | 1 | +5 to Ambient Attunement (passive Perception). You may read lips at normal conversational distance. You gain Resonant Fortune on Perception Active Resonances in dim light. |
| **Loom-Touched** | 4 | Once per Deep Attunement as an Instinct, perceive nearby Fate Numbers as coloured aura within 30 ft. You do not know the exact numbers, but you can see if any are within 3 points of your own (golden aura) or carry the Hollow Serpent resonance (dark frequency visible only to you). |
| **Void-Resistant** | 4 | Resonant Fortune on Warding Resonances against Void-Touched Exposure. Deep Attunement removes 2 stacks instead of 1. Weep-Stone charges used on you remove 3 stacks instead of 2. |
| **Path Initiate** | 4 | Prerequisite: Depth 5+ in your primary Path. With a qualified instructor (Depth 8+ in the target Path) and 250 gm + 250 days training, gain one Depth 1 feature from a second Path. Does not grant advancement in that Path. |
| **Bond-Walker** | 4 | The required Fate Number proximity for Fated Bond tier advancement is reduced by 1 for bonds you are part of. A Quad Bond (normally requires 4 souls within 2 points) requires 4 souls within 3 points with you in the group. |
| **Tactical Reading** | 5 | Prerequisite: Depth 3. After observing a creature for one full Pulse in combat, you learn one of: their Guard Rating, their current Vitality estimate (high/medium/low/critical), or one ability they have not yet used. You may do this once per creature per encounter. |
| **Kindred Aspect** | 8 | After spending at least 1 month living within a Kindred community not your own, you may select one passive Kindred Trait from that Kindred's entry and apply it permanently. Consult your Game Master -- not all traits are transferable. |
| **Legendary Endurance** | 13 | Once per Deep Attunement when you fail a Warding Resonance, you may succeed instead. This cannot prevent Loom Test failures. |
| **Loom's Favour** | 1 | Gain 3 Fate Tokens per Deep Attunement. Spend one as a Reflex to reroll any d20 roll -- you must use the new result. Fate Tokens expire on Deep Attunement. |

**Adventuring Rules**

*These rules cover situations that occur outside of direct combat. They come up in most sessions and are worth knowing before you need them.*

**Travel Pace**

| **Pace** | **Distance/Day** | **Active Resonance** | **Effect** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Fast** | 30 miles | Resonant Discord on Perception | Cannot use Stealth. Exhausting if sustained for 3+ days. |
| **Normal** | 24 miles | None | Standard travel. Foraging and tracking Active Resonances possible. |
| **Slow** | 18 miles | None | Stealth possible. Cartographic mapping possible. Ceque node reading possible. |

**Light and Vision**

| **Condition** | **Effect** |
| --- | --- |
| **Bright light** | Full Perception capability. Standard Active Resonances. |
| **Dim light** | Resonant Discord on visual Perception Active Resonances. Ambient Attunement reduced by 5. Counts as Lightly Obscured. |
| **Darkness** | Cannot see without special vision. Resonant Discord on attacks and Active Resonances relying on sight. Attackers have Resonant Fortune against you. Counts as Heavily Obscured. |
| **Darkvision (Kindred trait)** | See in darkness as if dim light; see in dim light as if bright light. Colour is absent in darkvision -- only shades of grey. Te Kapo and Dunmarim have this trait. |
| **Void-Sense (Te Kapo trait)** | Sense Void-adjacent presences (Void-Husks, Coil operatives, Hollow Serpent signals) within 60 ft regardless of light conditions. Does not replace vision. |

**Physical Hazards**

| **Hazard** | **Rule** |
| --- | --- |
| **Falling** | 1d6 bludgeoning damage per 10 ft fallen (max 20d6 at 200 ft). Landing on a soft surface (deep water, heavy snow, etc.): halve damage. Swiftness Warding Resonance (DC 15) on a fall of 20 ft or less to take no damage if you have safe surfaces to catch yourself on. |
| **Suffocating** | A creature can hold its breath for 1 + Endurance modifier minutes (minimum 30 seconds). After this: 0 Vitality at the start of its next Moment. |
| **Drowning** | A drowning creature begins making END Warding Resonances (DC 10 + 1 per prior roll). Failure: 1d6 damage and cannot act until breathing resumes. |
| **Extreme Cold** | Without cold-weather gear: END Warding Resonance (DC 10) each hour. Failure: 1 level of Exhaustion. |
| **Extreme Heat** | Without water (1 gallon/day required): END Warding Resonance (DC 5 + 1 per prior roll) each hour. Failure: 1 level of Exhaustion. |
| **Starvation** | After going without food for 3 + Endurance modifier days: gain 1 level of Exhaustion for each day beyond that. |
| **Encumbrance (optional)** | Carrying capacity = Forcefulness score x 15 lbs. Carrying more than half this: Resonant Discord on Swiftness and Forcefulness Active Resonances. Exceeding maximum: Speed becomes 5 ft. |

**Ceque Navigation**

Ceque nodes are the Precursor civilisation's grid infrastructure. A Ceque-Walker (or any character with the Ceque Line Born origin) can navigate by the grid. Active Resonance (Attunement or Aetheric Lore, Threshold 12) when near a node: determine distance and direction to the nearest active node, sense whether a node is reactivating (dangerous), and in the Boreal Expanse identify rune-marked paths between nodes.

**Languages and Tools**

*Every character begins with Common Trade plus any languages from their Origin. Additional languages can be learned through downtime (250 gm + 250 days) or in-world immersion at the Game Master's discretion.*

**Languages of the Known World**

| **Language** | **Typical Speakers** | **Script** | **Notes** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Common Trade** | All Kindreds (second language for most) | Common (Latin-adjacent) | The Duchy Compact's shared commercial language. Everyone who trades internationally speaks it. Accent identifies region. |
| **Dunmarim** | Dunmarim Kindred; Stone Kingdom traders | Dunmarim (runic derivative) | Pre-dates Common Trade by two thousand years. Includes technical mining and metallurgical vocabulary that has no equivalent elsewhere. |
| **Jade Script (written) / Jade Spoken (oral)** | Jade Empire denizens; Psi-Warrior tradition | Jade ideographic | Oral and written forms diverged significantly. Knowing Jade Spoken does not grant Jade Script literacy. |
| **Elder Futhark (Norse Runic)** | Boreal Expanse Kindreds; Giant-Kin runic tradition | Runic alphabet | Functional language for Boreal Expanse navigation and trade. Rune-marks on Giant-Kin skin are a dialect of this script. |
| **Waka-Tongue** | Moana-kin wayfinders; Southern Sea Circuit traders | No standard script (oral tradition) | Navigation-heavy vocabulary. Includes terms for celestial positioning, current systems, and wind patterns with no Common Trade equivalents. |
| **Ashé-Spoken** | Ashélands Kindreds; Orisha-Touched lineages | Ashé ideographic (shrine use only) | Carries tonal meaning -- the same syllable in different registers has different significance. Written form is ritual-only. |
| **K'uh-la'an Petal** | Southern Sea Circuit; Moon-Petal Lotus traders | Petal notation (botanical-based) | Trade language of the Southern Sea botanical economy. Encodes plant quality, medicinal preparation, and harvest conditions in conversational grammar. |
| **Serpent Cant** | Serpent-Kin internal community; some Coil operatives | Serpent glyph (body-mark system) | A partially physical language -- certain concepts require gesture or scale-pattern display for full meaning. Written form is an approximation. |
| **Void-Adjacent (Te Kapo)** | Te Kapo Kindred only | None -- purely oral | Encodes spatial relationships relative to Void-adjacent geometry rather than standard cardinal directions. Untranslatable except by other Te Kapo. |
| **Elder Kallos (Ancient)** | No living native speakers | Kallos pictographic (Precursor) | The language of the civilisation that built the Ceque grid. All surviving Precursor texts are in this script. The Comet-Mage tradition and the Order of Pure Reason both maintain working knowledge. |
| **Avian Trill** | Avian Kindred (dialect varies by wing-type lineage) | None (tonal/pitch-based) | Carries melody as grammatical structure. Humanoids without pitch discrimination can learn vocabulary but not full grammar. |

**Tool Proficiencies**

*Tool proficiency means you can use the tool with the relevant Attribute and your Mastery Bonus. Without proficiency you can attempt to use a tool but with Resonant Discord on the roll and cannot produce Mastery-quality work.*

| **Tool Category** | **Tools in Category** |
| --- | --- |
| **Artisan's Tools** | Alchemist's supplies, Calligrapher's supplies, Carpenter's tools, Cartographer's tools, Cobbler's tools, Cook's utensils, Glassblower's tools, Herbalism kit, Jeweler's tools, Leatherworker's tools, Mason's tools, Painter's supplies, Potter's tools, Smith's tools, Tinker's tools, Weaver's tools, Woodcarver's tools |
| **Navigation Tools** | Navigator's tools (sea), Surveyor's tools (land), Ceque-Walking compass (reads grid resonance; required for advanced Ceque Line Walking downtime) |
| **Stealth and Security Tools** | Thieves' tools, Forgery kit, Disguise kit, Poisoner's kit, Dead-drop materials (Fang of the Whisper network) |
| **Instruments** | Drum, flute, horn, lute, sitar (Jade Empire), viol, hand drum (Ashélands), bone-flute (Te Kapo) |
| **Gaming Sets** | Dragon's Eye (dice game; common in Duchy Compact taverns), Zodiac Cards (strategy card game; Kallos-Sworn favour this), Orisha Tiles (board game; played in the Ashélands) |
| **Accord-Maker Specific** | Infusion Kit (required for applying Infusions during Brief Attunement), Blueprint Survey Tools (required for Tier III+ Blueprint construction in the field) |
| **Investigation Tools** | Healer's kit (10 uses; stabilise Loom-Tested without Medicine Active Resonance), Aetheric Survey tools (measure Aetheric density; required for some Stellar Cartographer abilities) |

**Primal Essence Reference**

*Primal Essence is the soul's fundamental Aetheric orientation, rolled at character creation on 1d6. It is not alignment -- it is more fundamental than values. An evil Alpha is still Alpha. A compassionate Omega is still Omega. Essence shapes how the Fated Bond recognition feels and has mechanical weight in some Path and Bond abilities.*

| **Roll** | **Essence** | **Frequency** | **Bonus** | **Narrative Expression** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **1** | **Alpha** | ~1 in 6 | + 2 Resonance when leading a group (Disciplines, Active Resonances) | *Leaders, initiators, vanguards. Not necessarily domineering -- some lead by example, some by force, some by being the first to speak. On Fated Bond recognition: feel **"**seen for the first time.**"* |
| **2-5** | **Beta** | ~4 in 6 | None (most reliable, most adaptable) | *The backbone of every institution. Most characters are Beta. The Kallos-Sworn's institutional memory is primarily Beta. Drava Nullsong -- the Coil Triad's load-bearing wall -- is Beta. On Bond recognition: feel **"**finally understanding what they were maintaining.**"* |
| **6** | **Omega** | ~1 in 6 | +1 to Warding Resonances vs. cosmic / Fate effects | *Pattern-seekers, synthesisers, the ones who hold contradictions. An Omega parent in a bonded pair: children often manifest their Essence before age five. On Bond recognition: feel **"**the pattern completing.**"* |

| *Essence is rolled, never chosen. It represents the soul's resonance orientation as determined by the Loom -- not something the character decided about themselves. Players who strongly dislike their result can discuss with the Game Master, but the Loom's weave is what it is.* |
| --- |

*** Activities are highly sensitive to current world state, faction relationships, and campaign events. ***Standard activities remain available in most circumstances. Campaign-scale activities may require specific narrative prerequisites established during play. When in doubt, consult your Game Master.*

| **Activity** | **Time / Cost** | **Description** | **Availability** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Crafting** | 1+ days; half market price in materials | Produce items. Progress: 5 gm/day of work value. Accord-Maker items use Blueprint rules instead. | *Most locations* |
| **Practicing a Profession** | 1+ days; free | Earn 1 gm/day (Modest lifestyle). Mastered Discipline in relevant Profession: 2 gm/day. | *Most locations* |
| **Recuperating** | 7 days; Modest lifestyle | Remove 1 Exhaustion level. Resonant Fortune on recovery Warding Resonances vs. disease and poison. | *Safe location* |
| **Researching** | 1+ days; 1 gm/day library access | Game Master determines depth of information available based on library and topic. | *Library or archive required* |
| **Training (Discipline)** | 250 gm + 250 days | Gain a new Mastered Discipline. Requires a willing instructor. | *Most settled locations* |
| **Training (Tool / Language)** | 250 gm + 250 days | Gain Mastery in a tool or a new language. | *Most settled locations* |
| **Training (Weapon Category)** | 250 gm + 250 days | Gain Mastery in a weapon category you currently lack. Requires an instructor willing to teach you. | *Most settled locations* |
| **Carousing** | 1d6 x 10 gm spent | Build social network. Risk: Resonant Discord on Warding Resonance vs. mishap. | *Urban areas* |
| **Gambling** | Wager of choice | Insight Active Resonance vs. Game Master DC. Win: double wager; Lose: lose wager. | *Urban areas* |
| **Running a Business** | Requires property | 30d10 gm/month income minus operating costs (lifestyle x crew). | *Requires property* |
| **Selling Magical Items** | 1d4 weeks; varies | Find buyer. Price negotiated via Persuasion or Deception Active Resonance. | *Urban centres* |
| **Spreading Rumors** | 1+ days; no cost | Plant information in local networks. Social Active Resonance determines reach and accuracy. | *Most locations* |
| **Work (Bardic Performance)** | 1+ days; no cost | Mastered Performance: earn 1 gm/day and gain a social contact. Access to higher social circles over time. | *Urban or cultural centres* |
| **Aetheric ****&**** World-Specific Activities** |
| *** Aetheric Research*** Weave-capable* | 1+ weeks; 50 gm/week library access | Access Conclave or Temple library. Learn one new Working or Lore item per week. Comet-Mage Formulation Scribing uses this framework. | *Conclave / Temple access required* |
| *** Blueprint Construction*** Accord-Maker focus* | 1 hr per Blueprint tier; material cost varies | Construct a Blueprint object during downtime. Materials must be physically sourced (Dunmarim metals, Jade Empire crystal arrays, K'uh-la'an Weep-Stone). Supplier relationships become campaign infrastructure and faction hooks -- not abstract gold costs. | *Safe workshop; materials sourced* |
| **Infusion Application*** Accord-Maker* | During Brief Attunement; no gold cost | Apply Infusions to items instead of resting during a Brief Attunement. Cannot do both simultaneously. Infusions persist until Deep Attunement resets them. | *Brief Attunement; artisan tools in hand* |
| *** Kanya Siddha Purification*** All* | 1 hour; 50 gm/session | Remove 4 Lead-Scale Corruption levels (the only reliable treatment for Stages 3–4). Requires a Kanya-affiliated practitioner (Virgo territory, Temple of the Queen Bee, wandering Siddha). Cannot self-administer. | ** Kanya practitioner required* |
| **Fated Bond Acknowledgment Ceremony*** All bonded* | 1 day; no cost | Formally advance a Fated Bond tier after trigger conditions are met. Both parties must be present. Game Master narrates the ritual. A Denied Bond can be released here if both parties consent. | *Both parties willing and present* |
| *** Ceque Line Walking*** All* | 1 week per node; no cost | Travel and meditate on Precursor grid nodes. Builds toward Cross-Cultural Feat Variant at Depth 8. Blocked in Aether-Dampening Ore zones. | ** Active Ceque node accessible* |
| *** Legendary Beast Vigil (Your Sign)*** All* | 2d4 weeks; travel costs | Seek your sign's Legendary Beast to fulfil Zodiac Attunement prerequisites. Game Master narrates encounter -- not guaranteed. The Beast is not a quest objective. It encounters what it chooses to encounter. | ** Beast territory accessible* |
| *** Legendary Beast Encounter (Non-Sign)*** All* | 3d6 weeks; travel costs | Deliberately seek a Beast other than your sign's for a Secondary Attunement gift. The Beast has no cosmic reason to welcome you -- rarer and more dangerous than a sign encounter. | ** Beast territory accessible; risky* |
| **Crafting ****&**** Construction** |
| *** Precursor Site Excavation*** All* | 1d4 weeks per site; travel costs | Archaeological work at Elethorn ruins or Ceque node sites. Recover lost Blueprint schematics, Formulation fragments, or Precursor materials. Sites are actively contested by the Order of Pure Reason and Coil operatives. Results determined by Game Master. | ** Site accessible; faction conflict likely* |
| *** Resonant Node Stabilizer (Accord-Maker)*** Accord-Maker* | 1 week; 5,000 gm + Weep-Stone charges | Construct the specialized Blueprint device that can suppress a reactivating Ceque node for up to 72 hours. Requires Tier IV Blueprint access and either Grand Prime Forgeman instruction or Precursor documents. The only non-Ceque-Keeper tool that can buy time for the Resonant Binding ritual. | ** Blueprint access required; Grid-Point Seven context* |
| **Faction ****&**** Political Activities** |
| *** Faction Standing Work*** All* | 2+ weeks; lifestyle costs | Dedicate downtime to visible service for a named faction: Kallos-Sworn, Order of Pure Reason, Loom of Fate, a Zodiac temple, regional lord, or Coil front operation. Builds standing for access and alliances. The faction's enemies notice simultaneously. | ** Faction relationship required; location-specific* |
| *** Kallos-Sworn Initiation Preparation*** All (D3+ recommended)* | 2+ weeks; mentor required | Prepare for the Kallos-Sworn oath -- requires a mentor who has already sworn, study of approach protocols for your sign's Beast, and the journey itself. The oath scene (swearing "never again" in the Beast's presence) is a full session narrative event, not a roll. The Beast does not officiate. It does not respond. You speak into its presence and survive. | ** Kallos-Sworn mentor required; Beast territory accessible* |
| *** Loom of Fate Archive Access*** All* | 1+ weeks; significant political capital or favour | Access the Loom's Fate Number records -- the most complete in the world. Possible uses: identify bond clusters in your region, research a specific NPC's Number, learn what is already on record about your own. Cost: a favour from an insider, or political capital from a faction the Loom respects. Risk: you now have a file in their archive. | ** Loom contact or political leverage required* |
| *** Orisha Shrine Service*** All (Ashé-Medium focus)* | 1+ weeks; no gold cost | Work within an Orisha shrine community: tending the shrine, conducting minor rituals, building standing in the patron's network. Restores Ashé Vessel above standard maximum for 1 week after returning to active play. Builds contacts across the Ashélands' shrine network. The ritual economy runs on reciprocity -- what you give shapes what you receive. | ** Ashélands or shrine community accessible* |
| *** Starbound Bond Ritual*** Two willing participants* | 1 week ritual; 1+ month prior cooperation required | The Kallos-Sworn's Manufactured Resonance Project procedure. Creates an artificial Fated Bond thread between two willing participants who have actively cooperated for at least 1 month. Not as powerful as a natural bond at equivalent tier. Visible to Stellar Cartographers as manufactured -- different colour and texture from cosmic bonds. Legally binding in Kallos-Sworn order law. | ** Kallos-Sworn knowledge access required; both parties present* |
| **Intelligence ****&**** Espionage** |
| **Dead Letter Network Maintenance*** Shadow paths; all* | 1+ weeks; 10 gm/week upkeep | Maintain an intelligence infrastructure: check dead drops, cultivate informants, update cover identities. A well-maintained network provides one standing question per session routed through it. A neglected network (3+ weeks without maintenance) generates unreliable intelligence and risks being burned by the Fang of the Whisper. | *Network previously established* |
| *** Ashen Coil Intelligence*** All* | 1d4 weeks; no gold cost | Make contact with a Coil informant. Deception/Insight contest vs. Fang operative (DC 18). Success: learn 1d3 pieces of Coil movement intelligence. Failure: flagged as a target. Critical failure: the Fang of the Whisper learns your Fate Number. | ** Risky; contact required* |
| *** Void-Husk Study*** Coil-Stalker, Void-Hunter; all with access* | 3 days; access to restrained Husk | Careful observation of a captured Void-Husk. Learn: the Coil operation that produced it, its last assigned region, and whether it carries a Hollow Serpent signal (Aethar has been paying attention to that area). Risk: END Warding Resonance DC 13 daily or gain 1 Void-Touched Exposure stack as the Hollow Serpent pushes back through the Husk. | ** Restrained Husk required; isolated location* |
| **Path-Specific Activities** |
| **Lead-Scale Reduction Regimen*** Coil-Stalker* | 1 week; 3 Weep-Stone charges | Systematic gauge reduction through combined Weep-Stone usage and meditative discipline. Reduce gauge by 1d6+1 (vs. standard -2 from Deep Attunement alone). Requires a quiet, Coil-free location. Cannot be rushed -- attempting in hostile territory has no effect. | *Quiet, Coil-free location required* |
| **Geode Heart Recalibration*** Gear-Forged* | 1 week (with Accord-Maker) or 2 weeks solo | Recalibrate your Geode heart's zodiac frequency weighting. Adjust one Kindred-Zodiac Resonance ability to function as if your sign is the secondary attunement for 1 month. Represents deliberate identity work -- the Gear-Forged choosing which frequency to emphasise. | *Accord-Maker recommended; quiet conditions* |
| **Omote-Ura Balance Recalibration*** Wolf-Shifter* | 1 week; guide required | Guided meditation with a Siddha practitioner or Primal Accord character to consciously reset your Omote-Ura gauge starting position. Shift your default gauge by 2 up or down for 1 month. Cannot be performed alone -- the guide provides the external reference point your own perception cannot supply. | *Siddha or Primal Accord guide required* |
| **Kindred Cultural Immersion*** All* | 1 month; lifestyle costs | Live within a Kindred community not your own. Gain Resonant Fortune on social Active Resonances with that Kindred indefinitely. After 3 months: gain one cultural Discipline Mastery from that community's tradition. After 6 months: may qualify for the Cross-Cultural Zodiac Feat Variant if zodiac study is integrated. The community forms opinions about you. Those opinions travel. | *Community willing to accept you; location-specific* |
| **Siddha Mantra and Mudra Study*** Rāśi-Siddha; Tapas-adjacent paths* | 250 gm + 250 days; master required | Deep study of specific Siddha techniques to unlock new Tapas applications -- alternative Tapas uses, expanded Rajasic options, or reduced Tamasic costs. Requires a Rāśi-Siddha master willing to teach. The tradition does not recruit; the student must be worthy of the teacher's attention. | *Rāśi-Siddha master willing to teach* |
| **Campaign-Scale Activities** |
| *** Resonant Binding Ritual Component Work*** Various (component-specific)* | 2 weeks per component; component-specific prerequisites | Prepare individual components of the Resonant Binding ritual that seals Ophiuchus's fragment. Six components: Ceque-Walker circuit (Accord-Maker/Resonant Architect), Stellar Cartographer's Fate Number mapping, Ashé-Medium anchor ritual, kinetic component (Rāśi-Siddha or Primal Jarl), Weaving-under-pressure element (Comet-Mage), bond-witness requirement (any Triad-tier bonded group). Each prepared component reduces the final ritual's difficulty by 1 tier. | ** Component-specific prerequisites; campaign context required* |
| **Moon-Petal Lotus Cultivation*** All; Southern Sea Circuit location* | 1 growing season (3 months); 50 gm setup costs | Cultivate Moon-Petal Lotus in appropriate climate (Southern Sea Circuit region only). On success: 1d4 blooms per season (800-1,200 gm each on Terra Firma markets; strategic value beyond price). On failure: crop lost. Risk: the bloom's value makes the operation a target for the K'uh-la'an Petal-Weaver Castes and the Coil's supply-chain operatives. | ** Southern Sea Circuit or equivalent climate only* |
| *** Order of Pure Reason Consultation*** All; especially non-Weave-capable* | 1 week; significant concession or access fee | Engage the Order for research that benefits from their anti-Weaving scientific framework. They can explain Aetheric mechanics that orthodox sources won't acknowledge and identify properties of Aether-Dampening Ore that practitioners miss. Cost: a concession, a sample, or access to your Path's workings for their records. Risk: they now have a file on your Aetheric profile. They will study you whether you consent or not. | ** Order of Pure Reason accessible; concession required* |

**Green **= Sideros-specific activity.  *** ***= Availability highly dependent on campaign state -- consult your Game Master.*

| **Note on Availability** *Not all downtime activities listed here will be available at every point in the campaign. Availability depends on current world state, location, faction relationships, and what the campaign has established. Activities marked with an asterisk (*) are particularly sensitive to these factors. When in doubt about whether an activity is accessible, consult your Game Master before committing time and resources.* |
| --- |

**Downtime Activities**

**Campaign Tracking**

**Aethar's Five Stages**

| *The Serpent Bearer's plan is not guesswork -- it is documented in recovered Coil intelligence and Serath's private records. Stage 5 is not written in any Coil document; it exists only in Aethar's knowledge of the Ifa prophecy. Track which stages are active, complete, or disrupted by the party's actions.* |
| --- |

| **Stage** | **Description** | **Current Status / Notes** | **Party Impact** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Stage 1** | Accelerate Void-Husk production across Kindred populations to create chaos, fear, and political pressure on zodiac institutions |  |  |
| **Stage 2** | Destabilise the zodiac political blocs. The Leonine succession crisis is Stage 2 already in motion -- Lord Leo's legitimacy fracturing is not coincidence. |  |  |
| **Stage 3** | Seize the Crystalline Core beneath Argent Spire. The Three Conclaves' combined Aetheric pressure is the only thing keeping it sealed. Remove them. |  |  |
| **Stage 4** | Void the Loom itself -- sever the cosmic framework so that Fate stops weaving futures Aethar cannot control. |  |  |
| **Stage 5 (UNWRITTEN)** | *Prevent the Quint Bond from forming. The Fang of the Whisper's secondary mission: track bonded lineages, ensure the five never occupy the same location simultaneously.* | *SERATH KNOWS. Serath has identified 3 of 5 members and has not reported this to Aethar.* |  |

**Fated Bond Tiers**

| **Tier** | **Name** | **# Proximity** | **Key Abilities** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **I** | **Paired Bond** | Within 5 pts | Resonant Awareness (emotional state, unlimited range, same plane); Resonant Fortune on 1 Warding Resonance per Brief Attunement within 30 ft; Knowledge Transfer after 6 months; Synchronized Combat after 3 major encounters |
| **II** | **Triad Bond** | 3 souls, all within 4 pts | All Tier I. Whisper Bond telepathy (intent, sensation, same plane); Vitality transfer (half damage redirected as Reflex); Aetheric Channel Sharing (Weave-capable member loans Channel through bond) |
| **III** | **Quad Bond** | 4 souls, all within 2 pts | All Tier I-II. Full wordless communication; Death Resistance (drop to 1 Vitality instead of 0 while any conscious member in proximity); bond breach causes Aetheric discharge (structural damage in 300 ft radius) |
| **IV** | **Quint Bond** | 5 souls, all within 1 pt | All prior tiers at maximum. Aetheric Sovereignty (persistent Legendary Beast-scale field within 1 mile). Fate Sight (perceive Loom probability threads directly). Resonant Survival (no member reaches 0 Vitality while any other is conscious -- unconditional at Legendary Depth III). |

| **Special Rule** | **Detail** |
| --- | --- |
| **Void-Touched Numbers (13, 66, 99)** | Bond abilities operate at ONE tier higher than the bond tier. Bond is unstable (Game Master rolls d6 each session for unusual bond effect). Stellar Cartographers see the Hollow Serpent's frequency behind the Number when reading it. |
| **The Denied Bond** | A recognised but deliberately refused bond traps both parties in mounting instability. Alphas: erratic and reckless. Betas: controlling and resentful. Omegas: withdrawn and obsessive. Releasing it requires BOTH parties' willing participation. |
| **Loom Test conversion** | A bonded partner within 30 ft converts one Loom Test failure to a success per Pulse -- the bond's literal weight on the Loom. |
| **Aethar's intelligence on bonds** | The Fang of the Whisper tracks bonded lineages. If any party member's Fate Number is within 3 points of others at the table, Aethar has a file on it. |

