✶  ✶  ✶
**QUICK REFERENCE**
*Sideros Reference  |  Page XVIII*

| **✶  CORE TERMINOLOGY  ✶** **SIDEROS TERM** **MEANING** **Resonance Depth** Character Level **Mastery Bonus** Proficiency Bonus **Vitality** Hit Points **Guard Rating** Armour Class **Pulse Order** Initiative **Active Resonance** Skill Check / Attack Roll **Warding Resonance** Saving Throw **Discipline** Skill **Aetheric Channels** Spell Slots **Working** Spell **Weaving** Casting Magic **Instinct** Bonus Action **Resonant Fortune** Advantage **Resonant Discord** Disadvantage **Brief Attunement** Short Rest **Deep Attunement** Long Rest **Fated Bond** NPC Relationship **Kindred / Path / Calling** Race / Class / Subclass **✶  ATTRIBUTES  ✶** **ABBR.** **ATTRIBUTE** **GOVERNS** **FOR** **Forcefulness** Strength, physical force, intimidation **SWI** **Swiftness** Dexterity, speed, finesse **END** **Endurance** Constitution, resilience, fortitude **ACU** **Acuity** Intelligence, knowledge, investigation **ATT** **Attunement** Wisdom, perception, empathy **RES** **Resonance** Charisma, force of fate, social | **✶  CORE FORMULAS  ✶** **FORMULA** **CALCULATION** **Active Resonance** d20 + Attr mod + Mastery Bonus (if Mastered) **Warding Resonance** d20 + Attr mod (+ MB if Path grants Mastery) **Strike Resonance** d20 + Attr mod + MB  vs.  target Guard Rating **Pulse Order** d20 + Swiftness modifier  (resets each Pulse) **Guard Rating (standard)** 10 + SWI modifier + armor bonus **Guard Rating (Siddha)** 10 + ATT modifier + MB  (full Tapas pool) **Guard Rating (Gear-Forged)** 10 + END modifier **Ambient Attunement** 10 + ATT modifier + MB (if Perception Mastered) **Working Threshold DC** 8 + Mastery Bonus + Weaving Attribute modifier **Working Strike Bonus** Mastery Bonus + Weaving Attribute modifier **Vitality at D1** Roll Vita Die + END modifier (minimum 1) **Vitality per Depth** Roll Vita Die + END modifier; add to total **✶  DIFFICULTY THRESHOLDS (DT)  ✶** Very Easy **5** Easy **10** Moderate **15** Hard **20** Very Hard **25** Nearly Impossible **30** **✶  ACTION ECONOMY  ✶** **Act: **Primary Act per Moment — Strike, Weave, Grapple, Dash, Use Item, Help **Instinct: **Secondary action per Moment — Path Instinct features, minor actions **Reflex: **Triggered response; once per Pulse; occurs off your Moment **Movement: **Up to Speed in feet; can split around Acts. Not an action. **Free Interaction: **Drop item, speak, or minor object interaction — no cost **✶  RESONANT STRIKE ****&**** MISS  ✶** Resonant Strike (nat 20): Roll all damage dice twice. A natural 20 is always a hit. Critical Miss (nat 1): Always fails. Game Master may add complication. **✶  FORTUNE ****&**** DISCORD  ✶** **Resonant Fortune: **Roll 2d20, take the higher result **Resonant Discord: **Roll 2d20, take the lower result *Multiple Fortune sources give one Fortune die, not additional dice. Fortune and Discord cancel.* **✶  WARDING RESONANCE ATTRIBUTE MAPPING  ✶** **ATTRIBUTE** **USED AGAINST** **Forcefulness (FOR)** Physical force, being knocked back, crushing effects **Swiftness (SWI)** Explosions, breath weapons, area effects (can be dodged) **Endurance (END)** Poison, disease, exhaustion, death effects, constitution **Acuity (ACU)** Illusions, mind-affecting effects requiring logical resistance **Attunement (ATT)** Charms, scrying, emotional manipulation, Aetheric influence **Resonance (RES)** Fear, social coercion, Fated Bond contests, Void corruption **✶  WEAPON MASTERY  ✶** **Mastered** Full Mastery Bonus on Strike Resonance attack AND damage **Half-Mastered** Half Mastery Bonus (rounded down) on attack rolls only **Unmastered** Resonant Discord (2d20 lower) on ALL Strike Resonances **Armor (no Mastery)** Resonant Discord on all FOR + SWI Active Resonances & Wardings **✶  SUSTAINED RESONANCE (CONCENTRATION)  ✶** One Sustained Working at a time (Gemini Attunement: two). When you take damage while sustaining, make an END Warding Resonance (DC 10 or half damage, whichever is higher). Fail = Working ends. Drops if unconscious. End freely as a Free Interaction. **✶  THE STILLNESS (AETHER-DAMPENING ORE)  ✶** **Weave-capable** Resonance-Locked — cannot Weave any Working inside the zone **Aetheric Artifacts** Suppressed — magical bonuses inactive **Black Iron weapons** Unaffected — retain full effectiveness in Stillness zones **Gear-Forged (Tier I Geode)** Fully suppressed. Tier III+: 50% capacity **Detection** Weave-capable feel it before entering (ATT check DC 12) **Range (Refined Ore)** 30 ft radius per unit; 60 ft Dunmarim-processed; stacks **✶  CONDITIONS QUICK REF  ✶** **Sight-Severed** Discord on sight attacks; foes have Fortune to hit you **Dread-Struck** Discord all rolls while source visible; cannot move toward it **Grappled** Speed 0; escape as Act (FOR/SWI contest vs grappler) **Seized** Speed 0 and cannot increase (Restrained equivalent) **Incapacitated** Cannot take Acts or Instincts; drops Sustained Resonances **Soul-Swayed** Treats source as trusted ally; cannot Strike Resonate it **Loom-Suspended** Unconscious (stable); auto-fail FOR/SWI; attacks have Fortune **Loom-Tested** Dying at 0 Vitality; d20 DC 10 each Moment; 3 failures = thread ends **Corrupted** 1d6 dmg/Moment; Discord attacks & checks; END Warding to end **Prone** Discord vs. ranged; melee foes have Fortune; stand = half Speed **Dazed** Discord all Resonances until start of your next Moment **Resonance-Locked** Cannot Weave or use Channel abilities (Ore zone or source) **Aetheric Depletion** L1-5: Discord → half dmg → no Workings → 1d10/Moment. Clears on Deep Attunement **Void-Touched Exposure** Per stack: Discord Insight; 3+ stacks: Core intrusive thoughts **Exhausted** L1: Discord checks / L2: Speed halved / L4: Max Vita halved / L6: Thread ends |
| --- | --- |

Sideros  |  Character Folio & Chronicle  |  sideros.world

✶  ✶  ✶
**COMBAT SITUATIONS REFERENCE**
*Reference  |  Page XIX*

| **✶  COVER  ✶** **COVER TYPE** **BONUS** **EXAMPLES** **Half Cover** +2 GR & SWI Wardings Blocks ~half body: low wall, furniture, friend **Three-Quarter** +5 GR & SWI Wardings Blocks ~3/4 body: portcullis, arrow slit, thick trunk **Full Cover** Cannot be directly targeted Completely concealed. Area effects may still reach **✶  VISION ****&**** LIGHT  ✶** **Bright Light** Normal. No penalties. Full Ambient Attunement. **Dim Light (Lightly Obscured)** Resonant Discord on visual Perception checks. Ambient Attunement -5. **Darkness (Heavily Obscured)** Resonant Discord on Strikes. Attackers have Resonant Fortune vs. you. Cannot target without special sense. **Darkvision** Darkness = dim light (no Discord). Dim light = bright light. No colour perception. Te Kapo & Dunmarim. **Void-Sense (Te Kapo)** Detect Void-adjacent presences within 60 ft regardless of light. Does not replace sight. **Blindsight** Perceive without sight within range. Not affected by darkness or invisibility. **✶  PHYSICAL HAZARDS  ✶** **Falling** 1d6 bludgeoning per 10 ft fallen (max 20d6). Land prone. Soft surface (deep water, snow): halve damage. SWI Warding DC 15 on falls ≤20 ft to take none. **Suffocating** Hold breath: 1 + END modifier minutes (min 30 sec). After: 0 Vitality at start of next Moment. **Drowning** END Warding Resonance DC 10 + 1/prior roll. Fail: 1d6 damage; cannot act until breathing resumes. **Extreme Cold** No cold gear: END Warding DC 10 each hour. Fail: 1 Exhaustion level. **Extreme Heat** No water (1 gal/day required): END Warding DC 5 + 1/prior roll each hour. Fail: 1 Exhaustion. **Starvation** 3 + END modifier days without food: gain 1 Exhaustion per additional day beyond that. **✶  MOVEMENT QUICK REFERENCE  ✶** **Difficult terrain** 2 ft movement per 1 ft traveled (mud, rubble, dense undergrowth, shallow water) **Stand from prone** Costs half your Speed for the Moment. If insufficient movement: cannot stand until next Moment **Climbing / swimming** Difficult terrain (costs double) unless you have a climb/swim speed **Long Jump (running)** Forcefulness modifier x 3 ft with 10+ ft approach; half distance standing **High Jump** Automatically 3 + Forcefulness modifier ft; Athletics can exceed this **Through enemy space** Only by Disengage Act, or if size difference is 2+ categories **Through ally space** Always possible; counts as difficult terrain | **✶  REFLEX STRIKE (OPPORTUNITY ATTACK)  ✶** When a creature within your melee reach moves out of reach WITHOUT Disengaging, you may spend your Reflex to make one Strike Resonance. Occurs the moment movement begins. One Reflex per Pulse. *DOES NOT TRIGGER: Teleportation (Loom-Pull Step, Stag Attunement). Disengage Action. Being moved by an external force (pushed, thrown, dragged).* **✶  GRAPPLE  ✶** Use an Act to make a Forcefulness Active Resonance vs. target's Forcefulness or Swiftness (their choice). Target must be no more than 1 size category larger than you. Require at least one free hand. Success: Target gains Grappled (Speed 0; Discord on Strikes vs. others). You may drag them at half Speed. Release as Free Interaction. Break free: target spends their Act to contest again. **✶  SHOVE  ✶** Use an Act (or replace one Strike in a multi-attack) to make a Forcefulness Active Resonance vs. target's Forcefulness or Swiftness (their choice). Target must be no more than 1 size larger. Success: Choose either — knock target Prone, OR push target 5 ft away from you. **✶  TWO-WEAPON FIGHTING  ✶** When you Strike with a light melee weapon in one hand, you may make one additional Strike with a different light melee weapon as an Instinct (not an Act). Add NO Attribute modifier to off-hand damage unless a Path feature specifically grants this. **✶  SURPRISE  ✶** If one side is unaware when combat begins, that side does NOT act in Pulse 1 — they spend the full Pulse becoming aware of the threat. Pulse Order is still rolled; their Moments simply pass. Feral Instinct trait (Beast-Kin) and certain Infusions prevent being surprised. **✶  PULSE ORDER TIE-BREAKING  ✶** When two combatants have the same Pulse Order result: (1) Higher Swiftness modifier acts first. (2) If still tied: higher Fate Number acts first. (3) If still tied: Game Master decides. Pulse Order resets each Pulse. **✶  SIZE CATEGORIES  ✶** **SIZE** **SPACE** **EXAMPLES** **Tiny** 2.5×2.5 ft Bat, cat, rat — does not occupy standard space **Small** 5×5 ft Halfling, gnome **Medium** 5×5 ft Human, most Kindreds **Large** 10×10 ft Horse, ogre **Huge** 15×15 ft Legendary Beasts (most) **Gargantuan** 20×20+ ft Ancient dragons, Abyssal Leviathan **✶  CEQUE NAVIGATION (SIDEROS-SPECIFIC)  ✶** Ceque nodes are Precursor grid infrastructure. A Ceque-Walker or Ceque Line Born origin character can navigate by the grid: make an ATT or Aetheric Lore Active Resonance (DT 12) near a node to: •  Determine distance and direction to the nearest active node •  Sense whether a node is reactivating (dangerous) •  In the Boreal Expanse: identify rune-marked paths between nodes •  Ceque Line Walking (Downtime: 1 week/node) builds toward the Cross-Cultural Feat at Depth 8 •  Blocked in Aether-Dampening Ore zones (Resonance-Locked) |
| --- | --- |

✶  ✶  ✶
**THE WORLD OF SIDEROS**
*World Primer  |  Page XX  |  For Players*

| **✶  THE WORLD OF SIDEROS  ✶** Sideros is in its fourth era — the Shattered Age. The twelve gods of the Pantheonic Council fell when Ophiuchus was corrupted by the Hollow Serpent and shattered. The remaining twelve gods chose to dissolve themselves into vast Aetheric presences rather than dissolve entirely: they became the Legendary Beasts. They no longer govern — but they remember, and they recognize mortals whose soul-frequency resonates with their domain. **✶  THE LOOM OF FATE  ✶** The Loom is a cosmic structure predating every civilization. It weaves probable futures from the Aether. Every creature has a Fate Number (1d100, permanent) marking their position in the Loom's pattern. Numbers that fall near each other are drawn toward Fated Bond relationships. Numbers near 13, 66, or 99 carry the Hollow Serpent's resonance. The primary antagonist, Aethar the Serpent Bearer, intends to destroy the Loom entirely. **✶  KEY FACTIONS  ✶** **Ashen Coil** Aethar’s organization. Publicly: trade syndicate & academic society. Privately: structured intelligence operation pursuing the Five Stages. Three layers: outer-ring agents (unknowing), inner-ring operatives (partial knowledge), Triad (full knowledge). Produces Void-Husks, controls Ore supply, tracks bond lineages to prevent the Quint Bond. **Kallos-Sworn** The twelve-house order preventing another Pantheonic catastrophe. Each house corresponds to a zodiac sign and a Legendary Beast. Centuries-long intelligence war against the Coil. Their institutional memory is primarily Beta. Arch-Oracle Lyra has calculated the Loom seal’s failure timeline. **Three Conclaves** The world’s three Weaving scholarly organizations. Their combined Aetheric pressure is the only thing keeping the Crystalline Core sealed. Shifting Horizons (Aethar’s former Conclave), Earthly Core, and Veil-Walkers. Destabilizing them is Aethar’s Stage 1 objective. **Loom of Fate org.** A Beta organization — patient, networked, invisible. Weaves fate at an institutional level. Fated Bonds form between souls in resonance regardless of alignment. The Ashen Coil’s internal bond is genuine, real, and one of the reasons they’re dangerous. **Order of Pure Reason** Dunmarim-affiliated. Anti-Aetheric ideology. Controls Aether-Dampening Ore production. Banned Weep-Stone import. Active conflict with the Coil over Ore supply chain control. **✶  THE QUINT BOND PROPHECY  ✶** *Five souls within 1 point of each other on the Fate Number scale. Never recorded in written history. The Ifá scripture names them **"**the Five Who Remember What the Gods Were.**"** Serath has identified 3 of 5 and withheld this information from Aethar for six weeks. The Fang of the Whisper’s true secondary mission is to prevent these five from ever occupying the same location simultaneously.* | **✶  LEGENDARY BEASTS ****&**** ZODIAC SIGNS  ✶** *Each Beast was once a god. Zodiac Attunement requires encountering your sign’s Beast within 300 ft (it must perceive you) and surviving with your Fate Number intact, then reaching Depth 4.* **SIGN** **LEGENDARY BEAST** **DOMAIN** **Aries** Ashen Ram Fire / Initiative **Taurus** Khalkotauros Earth / Endurance **Gemini** Twin-Serpents Air / Duality **Cancer** Adamant Crab Water / Protection **Leo** Nemean Lion Fire / Glory **Virgo** Queen Bee Earth / Healing **Libra** Great Roc Air / Balance **Scorpio** Stygian Scorpion Water / Secrets **Sagittarius** Star-Metal Stag Fire / Stars **Capricorn** Sea-Goat Earth / Mastery **Aquarius** Abyssal Leviathan Air / Depths **Pisces** Twin Dream-Fish Water / Dreams **✶  FATED BOND FORMATION — THREE STAGES  ✶** **Stage 1: Resonant Proximity** Passive and unconscious. Numbers near each other produce sharpened attention, unusual clarity. No mechanical benefit — narrative weight only. Stellar Cartographers can detect it. **Stage 2: The Kindle Moment** The Loom decides when — a shared moment of genuine significance: near-death, revelation, witnessed grief. Cannot be manufactured. The bond cannot form without it. **Stage 3: Acknowledgment** Both parties consciously name and accept the bond. A formal ceremony is available (1 day, no cost). Advances the bond to the next tier. A Denied Bond traps both in mounting instability. **✶  SESSION ZERO QUESTIONS  ✶** **What do you want?** *Not a goal — a want. Drives your Path choice.* **What have you lost?** *Every character is defined partly by absence. Drives Origin.* **What does the Loom want with you?** *You don’t have to know. But consider: do you feel watched?* **What do you know about the Ashen Coil?** *Everyone knows something. How wrong are you?* **Who would notice if you disappeared?** *Name one person, org, or creature. The Loom will use this.* |
